:"2019-10-19T01:24:57.003Z","updatedAt":"2020-10-28T16:08:22.736Z","environment":{"sys":{"id":"master","type":"Link","linkType":"Environment"}},"revision":4,"contentType":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"ContentType","id":"benefitType"}},"locale":"en-US"},"title":"Waived"}]},{"sys":{"space":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"Space","id":"abx5xo923wy6"}},"id":"6lPmajqjT4HfWuzdVGTcFZ","type":"Entry","createdAt":"2020-01-01T17:36:55.255Z","updatedAt":"2021-01-01T09:31:00.975Z","environment":{"sys":{"id":"master","type":"Link","linkType":"Environment"}},"revision":5,"contentType":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"ContentType","id":"sectionGroup"}},"locale":"en-US"},"cmsTitle":"Ext US Group - Medical","title":"Medical","content":[{"sys":{"space":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"Space","id":"abx5xo923wy6"}},"id":"3f21VaDllOGtBccGiP32I5","type":"Entry","createdAt":"2020-01-01T17:36:29.839Z","updatedAt":"2020-12-28T21:02:02.540Z","environment":{"sys":{"id":"master","type":"Link","linkType":"Environment"}},"revision":3,"contentType":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"ContentType","id":"sectionContent"}},"locale":"en-US"},"cmsTitle":"Ext US Section - Medical ","sectionDescription":"Just like different content is streamed around the globe, we recognize that medical benefits work differently based on the country you live in. No matter what the case is, we make sure that you’re covered. Netflix offers three medical plan options through Collective Health + Anthem and one plan through Kaiser so you can make the right decision for your lifestyle and healthcare needs."},{"sys":{"space":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"Space","id":"abx5xo923wy6"}},"id":"5Qd8jjYqRkDhmZTaIP9Mn2","type":"Entry","createdAt":"2020-01-01T17:36:33.721Z","updatedAt":"2020-12-28T21:20:58.984Z","environment":{"sys":{"id":"master","type":"Link","linkType":"Environment"}},"revision":4,"contentType":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"ContentType","id":"sectionContent"}},"locale":"en-US"},"cmsTitle":"Plan Options - US","sectionTitle":"Plan Options","sectionDescription":"All of the plans cover eligible preventive care at 100% when you use an in-network provider. The Collective Health + Anthem plans pay more of the cost when you use in-network  providers than if you use out-of-network providers, and the Kaiser plan only covers benefits for in-network  providers.\n\nConsider what’s important to you when choosing your coverage. Do you prefer a higher premium in exchange for lower, more predictable costs throughout the year? Or, would you prefer a lower premium with higher out-of-pocket expenses? The chart below highlights the features of each of the plans.\n\nYou can search if your provider is in Collective Health + Anthem's network [here](https://join.collectivehealth.com/netflix/getCare?planYear=2020\u0026selectedMedicalPlan=3311\u0026lat=37.25959\u0026lng=-121.96264\u0026locationQuery=100%20Winchester%20Cir,%20Los%20Gatos,%20CA%2095032-1815\u0026page=1\u0026geolocate=1).\n\n| Plan Name     | Plan Highlights     |\n| ---------- | ---------- |\n| __Collective Health + Anthem PPO1 Plan*__\u003c/br\u003e\u003c/br\u003e __Pay more now__ (i.e. more deducted from your allowance), __pay less later__ (i.e. at the doctor's office).       | Lowest deductible and out-of-pocket maximum, Highest premiums, Mental health and substance abuse/chemical dependency covered 90% after deductible, Pay a $25 copay for most services       |\n| __Collective Health + Anthem PPO2 Plan*__\u003c/br\u003e\u003c/br\u003e __Pay less now__ (i.e. less deducted from your allowance), __pay more later__ (i.e. at the doctor's office).       | Pay a $30 copay for most services       |\n| __Collective Health + Anthem High Deductible Plan with a Health Savings Account (HSA)*__\u003c/br\u003e\u003c/br\u003e __Pay less now__ than the other Collective Health + Anthem plans (i.e. less deducted from your allowance), __pay more than the other CH plans later__ (i.e. at the doctor's office). Only plan with pre-tax HSA.       | Lowest premiums, Tax-advantaged HSA available, Highest deductible, No flat copay; deductibles and cost sharing for all services       |\n| __Kaiser California HMO Plan__\u003c/br\u003e\u003c/br\u003e __Pay less than the Collective Health PPO plans now__ (i.e. less deducted from your allowance). __Pay a copay at each office visit later.__ Visit only Kaiser facilities and providers.        | In-network coverage only (except for emergencies), no deductible, Must choose a primary care physician to coordinate all care, Inpatient mental health and substance abuse/chemical dependency covered 100%       |\n*If you are outside of CA, your provider will submit claims to the local Blue Cross Blue Shield network. If you are based in Hawaii, [click here](https://employee.netflix.net/benefits/health/medical#hawaii-plans-hmsa \"Hawaii Plans ELP\") to see the plans available to you\n\n*[in-network]: In-network providers and facilities charge agreed-upon, lower, pre-negotiated fees.\n*[out-of-network]: Out-of-network providers can charge any amount for services, resulting in higher out-of-pocket costs. Maximum Reimbursable Charge limits apply.\n*[deductible]: The amount you pay each year before the plan shares the cost of your health services.\n*[copay]: The flat amount you pay under certain health plans for health services."},{"sys":{"space":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"Space","id":"abx5xo923wy6"}},"id":"1Z8qJKfCv5rMyG6uSwyPrk","type":"Entry","createdAt":"2020-01-01T17:36:36.493Z","updatedAt":"2020-09-25T21:25:46.584Z","environment":{"sys":{"id":"master","type":"Link","linkType":"Environment"}},"revision":4,"contentType":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"ContentType","id":"sectionContent"}},"locale":"en-US"},"cmsTitle":"Ext US Section - Medical - Plan Comparison Chart (Pt 1 of 2)","sectionDescription":"# __Plan Highlights__\n\n| **Benefit** | **Description** |\n| --- | --- |\n| **In-Network Preventive Care is covered 100%**.| Routine preventive physical exams, including related preventive screenings and immunizations, including flu shots. |\n| **Mental Health Support**. | Visits with psychiatrists, psychologists, therapists, clinical social workers, and marriage and family therapists are covered. Netflix also offers additional [behavioral health benefits](https://benefits.netflix.com/united-states#behavioral-health-support) outside of our medical plans. |\n| **Transgender Benefits** Expanded coverage in alignment with the WPATH standards of care and procedures that impact a person’s gender identity | Including, but not limited to: gender confirmation surgery, mastectomy with chest reconstruction (top surgery), scrotoplasty, phalloplasty, augmentation mammoplasty, hair removal, mental health, hormone replacement therapy, voice therapy and [more](https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/1OloYV6ykwTNAElPHIstQhY92TE51raPh9mnu2xbocfs/edit#gid=0). |\n| **Parental Services and Support** | Includes maternity services, free in-network breast pumps, and out-of-network breast pumps with the same cost sharing as in-network, up to an allowable amount under the medical plan. Fertility, Surrogacy, and Adoption services are covered outside of our medical plan with our [Family Forming benefit, Carrot](https://benefits.netflix.com/united-states/life-happens#family-forming).  |\n| **Physical Therapies, Treatments  and Rehabilitation Services** | Coverage includes Physical, Occupational, Speech Therapy and Cognitive and Respiratory Rehabilitation, Acupuncture and Chiropractic. Coverage varies by plan. |\n| **Telehealth** | As an alternative to an in-person office visit (and you’re enrolled in a Netflix medical plan), you and your covered dependents can use Telemedicine, which gives you 24/7 access to a doctor via phone or online video chat. |\n| **Prescription Drug (Rx)** | If you are enrolled in a Netflix medical plan, you can fill your prescriptions through retail pharmacies or take advantage of the mail order program for medications you take regularly. |\n\n# Plan Comparison Chart\n\nBelow is what you pay for in-network and out-of-network care.\n\nWhen you visit an out-of-network provider, you and the medical plan share the cost of your care. The plan determines what the Maximum Reimbursable Charge will be. If your provider charges more than that, you’re responsible for any amount that exceeds it."},{"sys":{"space":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"Space","id":"abx5xo923wy6"}},"id":"7CWWu871N0NBwUGOWGfujX","type":"Entry","createdAt":"2020-01-01T17:36:41.570Z","updatedAt":"2021-01-01T08:00:58.643Z","environment":{"sys":{"id":"master","type":"Link","linkType":"Environment"}},"revision":2,"contentType":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"ContentType","id":"googleVideo"}},"locale":"en-US"},"googleDriveId":"12-JCA4XPIvm8dmFaqpMOTBSWPSiu-uMGZZjcqFBVJNQ","orientation":true,"cmsTitle":"2021 - Medical - Plan Comparison Chart (Pt 2 of 2)"},{"sys":{"space":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"Space","id":"abx5xo923wy6"}},"id":"3cikgKZ7n8iiTbv0Rm9daZ","type":"Entry","createdAt":"2020-09-24T21:33:32.392Z","updatedAt":"2020-09-24T21:33:32.392Z","environment":{"sys":{"id":"master","type":"Link","linkType":"Environment"}},"revision":1,"contentType":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"ContentType","id":"sectionContent"}},"locale":"en-US"},"cmsTitle":"Ext - US Medical - Collective Health ","sectionTitle":"Collective Health","sectionDescription":"__What is Collective Health?__\nCollective Health is a benefits administrator that pairs its technology and its Member Advocates (who have a deep understanding of our plans and culture) with Anthem, Delta Dental, and VSP (traditional US medical insurance carriers) to empower decision making by employees, improve transparency, reduce distraction and complexity, and improve the healthcare experience for members. The Member Advocates will help Netflix employees receive proper care and resources, assist with transition of care (including previous prior authorizations), applying for Continuity of Care, and resolve claim issues and questions. Check out this [short clip](https://vimeo.com/234056590/f7fd9b8c2a \"Collective Health Intro Video\") to learn more about Collective Health.\n\n__Care Navigation__\nCollective Health also offers a Care Navigation program where their team of Social Workers and Pharmacists review your care plan, help with care coordination and provide resources and support. Members who typically need the support of Care Navigation are those managing conditions such as cancer, autism spectrum disorder, gender affirmation surgery, transplant surgery, and more. \n\nIf you or your dependent are seeking transgender-related care, Collective Health has a dedicated Care Navigator to assist our employees and their family members. "}]},{"sys":{"space":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"Space","id":"abx5xo923wy6"}},"id":"4GpTqEeWFXpeJRrowCmYOo","type":"Entry","createdAt":"2020-01-01T17:37:53.521Z","updatedAt":"2021-01-01T09:00:58.009Z","environment":{"sys":{"id":"master","type":"Link","linkType":"Environment"}},"revision":4,"contentType":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"ContentType","id":"sectionGroup"}},"locale":"en-US"},"cmsTitle":"Ext US Group - Dental","title":"Dental","content":[{"sys":{"space":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"Space","id":"abx5xo923wy6"}},"id":"25htp0Zh5c8BXBa9NPrca2","type":"Entry","createdAt":"2020-01-01T17:37:02.007Z","updatedAt":"2020-01-01T17:37:02.007Z","environment":{"sys":{"id":"master","type":"Link","linkType":"Environment"}},"revision":1,"contentType":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"ContentType","id":"sectionContent"}},"locale":"en-US"},"cmsTitle":"2020 - Dental - How It Works - US","sectionTitle":"How It Works","sectionDescription":"The Collective Health + Delta Dental Plan pays 100% of your preventive \u0026 diagnostic care such as exams, x-rays and fluoride applications, and a percentage of other services including fillings, crowns, implants and orthodontics for children and adults.\n1. The plan covers Diagnostic and Preventative care 100%.\n2. You pay the full cost of all other care until you meet the annual deductible. The deductibles are waived for Diagnostic and Preventative care and Orthodontics. \n3. Then the plan shares the cost with you.\n\nThe most the plan will pay for covered services per year is $2,000 per person. Diagnostic and Preventative (D\u0026P) and Orthodontics do not count toward the annual maximum of $2,000/per person.\n\nIf you use in-network providers, your costs will be lower because you pay a portion of the dentist's negotiated fees. This is the amount participating dentists have agreed to accept as payment in full.\n\nIf you use an out-of-network dentist, Collective Health + Delta Dental reimbursement is based on in-network contracted fees for Delta Dental PPO dentists. If your provider charges more than that, you're responsible for any amount exceeding the maximum reimbursable amount.\n\nTo see how much you'll pay for a service out of pocket, get a free predetermination. Your dentist can submit a predetermination to Delta Dental so you can make sure the plan covers a recommended procedure.\n\n*[deductible]: The amount you pay each year before the plan shares the cost of your health services.\n*[in-network]: In-network providers and facilities charge agreed-upon, lower, pre-negotiated fees.\n*[out-of-network]: Out-of-network providers can charge any amount for services, resulting in higher out-of-pocket costs. Maximum Reimbursable Charge limits apply.\n"},{"sys":{"space":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"Space","id":"abx5xo923wy6"}},"id":"47ZKIXof4XCbosSZki2FK5","type":"Entry","createdAt":"2020-01-01T17:37:05.276Z","updatedAt":"2020-12-28T21:02:45.576Z","environment":{"sys":{"id":"master","type":"Link","linkType":"Environment"}},"revision":2,"contentType":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"ContentType","id":"sectionContent"}},"locale":"en-US"},"cmsTitle":"Dental - US - Plan Details (Pt 1 of 2)","sectionTitle":"Plan Details","sectionDescription":"Here's more information on what is covered.\n"},{"sys":{"space":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"Space","id":"abx5xo923wy6"}},"id":"Cavn6PiRPFBPi89rXvTEu","type":"Entry","createdAt":"2020-01-01T17:37:08.949Z","updatedAt":"2021-01-01T08:00:58.092Z","environment":{"sys":{"id":"master","type":"Link","linkType":"Environment"}},"revision":2,"contentType":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"ContentType","id":"googleVideo"}},"locale":"en-US"},"googleDriveId":"17nsNz9aImdkBEjOJhD_qQWpWhVLw5ZVnouKOQPjTP98","orientation":true,"cmsTitle":"2021 - Dental - US - Plan Details (Pt 2 of 2)"},{"sys":{"space":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"Space","id":"abx5xo923wy6"}},"id":"407RGJwAeIwccb8ffTqAuW","type":"Entry","createdAt":"2020-01-01T17:37:11.918Z","updatedAt":"2021-01-01T08:00:59.719Z","environment":{"sys":{"id":"master","type":"Link","linkType":"Environment"}},"revision":2,"contentType":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"ContentType","id":"sectionContent"}},"locale":"en-US"},"cmsTitle":"2021 - Dental - US - Premiums","sectionTitle":"2021 Premiums","sectionDescription":"Here’s what you’ll pay each pay period in 2021 based on who you cover.  Use the cost calculator to see how the $16,000 allowance applies to you.\n\n| Coverage     | Premium     |\n| ---------- | ---------- |\n| Employee Only       | $22.00       |\n| EE + Spouse/DP or EE + Child(ren)       | $46.96       |\n| Employee + Family       | $84.38       |\n"}]},{"sys":{"space":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"Space","id":"abx5xo923wy6"}},"id":"1mTW9Frij4Z17D4SGqPht2","type":"Entry","createdAt":"2020-01-01T17:38:28.507Z","updatedAt":"2020-11-09T16:27:14.228Z","environment":{"sys":{"id":"master","type":"Link","linkType":"Environment"}},"revision":3,"contentType":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"ContentType","id":"sectionGroup"}},"locale":"en-US"},"cmsTitle":"2020 - Ext US Group - Vision","title":"Vision","content":[{"sys":{"space":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"Space","id":"abx5xo923wy6"}},"id":"6R2vSE0I1GnpycebmEwVox","type":"Entry","createdAt":"2020-01-01T17:38:12.012Z","updatedAt":"2020-01-01T17:38:12.012Z","environment":{"sys":{"id":"master","type":"Link","linkType":"Environment"}},"revision":1,"contentType":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"ContentType","id":"sectionContent"}},"locale":"en-US"},"cmsTitle":"2020 - How It Works - Vision - US","sectionTitle":"How It Works","sectionDescription":"Netflix offers a cost-effective vision plan through Collective Health + Vision Service Plan (VSP) that covers an annual exam and helps you save on prescription lenses, including specialty lenses and frames, or contact lenses.\n\n- You can use any provider you want (but you save money when you use a VSP provider).\n- If you use an **in-network provider**, you pay a flat copay based on the service received.\n- If you go **out-of-network**, the plan pays a set amount, and you pay the rest. You must pay the cost up front, and then file a claim for reimbursement.\n\n*[in-network]: In-network providers and facilities charge agreed-upon, lower, pre-negotiated fees.\n*[out-of-network]: Out-of-network providers can charge any amount for services, resulting in higher out-of-pocket costs. Maximum Reimbursable Charge limits apply."},{"sys":{"space":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"Space","id":"abx5xo923wy6"}},"id":"1RBh2E4whyvPvwdQDtHYTY","type":"Entry","createdAt":"2020-01-01T17:38:15.339Z","updatedAt":"2020-11-09T16:27:05.681Z","environment":{"sys":{"id":"master","type":"Link","linkType":"Environment"}},"revision":2,"contentType":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"ContentType","id":"sectionContent"}},"locale":"en-US"},"cmsTitle":"2020 - Vision Plan Details","sectionTitle":"Plan Details","sectionDescription":"Every calendar year, you can get a covered exam, plus prescription lenses, lens enhancements and frames OR you can get contact lenses in lieu of lenses and frames. Here's what you pay for care."},{"sys":{"space":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"Space","id":"abx5xo923wy6"}},"id":"7egw5HJWwKcfsUMdt6Q02y","type":"Entry","createdAt":"2020-01-01T17:38:18.406Z","updatedAt":"2021-01-01T08:00:59.841Z","environment":{"sys":{"id":"master","type":"Link","linkType":"Environment"}},"revision":2,"contentType":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"ContentType","id":"googleVideo"}},"locale":"en-US"},"googleDriveId":"1EVUffaM_0LPtias6r7akM2LET_BalV_Ik9ovdsa3NR8","orientation":true,"cmsTitle":"2021 - Vision - US - Plan Comparison Chart"},{"sys":{"space":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"Space","id":"abx5xo923wy6"}},"id":"6qnxQLZwWIeT41AVk8uZT6","type":"Entry","createdAt":"2020-01-01T17:38:21.456Z","updatedAt":"2021-01-01T08:00:58.856Z","environment":{"sys":{"id":"master","type":"Link","linkType":"Environment"}},"revision":2,"contentType":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"ContentType","id":"sectionContent"}},"locale":"en-US"},"cmsTitle":"2021 - US - Vision Premiums","sectionTitle":"2021 Premiums","sectionDescription":"Here’s what you’ll pay each pay period in 2021 based on who you cover.  Use the cost calculator to see how the $16,000 allowance applies to you.\n\n| Coverage     | Premium     |\n| ---------- | ---------- |\n| Employee Only       | $4.88       |\n| EE + Spouse/DP or EE + Child(ren)       | $8.54       |\n| Employee + Family       | $13.85       |\n\n*[premium]: The pre-tax amount you pay per paycheck for health insurance.\n*[premiums]: The pre-tax amount you pay per paycheck for health insurance."}]},{"sys":{"space":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"Space","id":"abx5xo923wy6"}},"id":"3D7yxlJ57mT6Bk1vHRmVxB","type":"Entry","createdAt":"2020-01-01T17:36:44.700Z","updatedAt":"2020-01-01T18:10:04.139Z","environment":{"sys":{"id":"master","type":"Link","linkType":"Environment"}},"revision":3,"contentType":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"ContentType","id":"sectionContent"}},"locale":"en-US"},"cmsTitle":"2020 - Ext US Section - ID Cards","sectionTitle":"ID Cards","sectionDescription":"Health, dental, and vision insurance cards will arrive at your home address 2–3 weeks after enrolling in Workday."},{"sys":{"space":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"Space","id":"abx5xo923wy6"}},"id":"4FXyZDP0bKwAKK466gYEgG","type":"Entry","createdAt":"2018-10-24T20:29:44.968Z","updatedAt":"2020-06-17T15:23:23.789Z","environment":{"sys":{"id":"master","type":"Link","linkType":"Environment"}},"revision":2,"contentType":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"ContentType","id":"sectionContent"}},"locale":"en-US"},"cmsTitle":"Ext US Section - Health Savings Account (HSA)","sectionTitle":"Health Savings Account (HSA)","sectionDescription":"Netflix offers a Health Savings Account (HSA) that is paired with our Collective Health + Anthem High Deductible Plan. An HSA is a triple-tax-advantaged account where you can contribute funds to the account on a pre-tax basis through payroll deductions. You can use these funds to pay for eligible healthcare, dental and vision expenses now and in the future, including copays and deductibles."},{"sys":{"space":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"Space","id":"abx5xo923wy6"}},"id":"2SnmSB9uUg6UEe80SYUmIM","type":"Entry","createdAt":"2018-10-24T20:31:16.459Z","updatedAt":"2018-10-24T20:31:16.459Z","environment":{"sys":{"id":"master","type":"Link","linkType":"Environment"}},"revision":1,"contentType":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"ContentType","id":"sectionContent"}},"locale":"en-US"},"cmsTitle":"Ext US Section - Flexible Spending Accounts (FSA)","sectionTitle":"Flexible Spending Accounts (FSA)","sectionDescription":"Flexible Spending Accounts (FSA) allow you to set aside pre-tax money to pay for eligible healthcare and dependent care expenses. Plan carefully, because you lose any money you don’t use at the end of the calendar year. You decide how much to contribute to your FSA(s) each year during Open Enrollment based on your unique needs."},{"sys":{"space":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"Space","id":"abx5xo923wy6"}},"id":"ggdabL3Xy0ackC68QWsgu","type":"Entry","createdAt":"2018-10-25T21:18:14.061Z","updatedAt":"2020-12-28T21:08:47.309Z","environment":{"sys":{"id":"master","type":"Link","linkType":"Environment"}},"revision":4,"contentType":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"ContentType","id":"sectionContent"}},"locale":"en-US"},"cmsTitle":"Ext Global Section - Mental Health Support","sectionTitle":"Mental Health Support","sectionDescription":"At Netflix, we know you want to produce work you are proud of. In order to perform your best, you have to feel your best. That is why we provide unlimited coaching through Ginger; meditation and mindfulness resources through Headspace; and access to free therapy, counseling, and work-life referrals through the EAP. With some health insurance plans, you may be able to utilize your medical benefits for additional therapy visits. Check out your medical plan to see if this is offered."},{"sys":{"space":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"Space","id":"abx5xo923wy6"}},"id":"4LgioRRcQ8KAAaWYaW8AiW","type":"Entry","createdAt":"2018-10-24T20:33:16.676Z","updatedAt":"2020-06-16T23:13:17.645Z","environment":{"sys":{"id":"master","type":"Link","linkType":"Environment"}},"revision":4,"contentType":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"ContentType","id":"sectionContent"}},"locale":"en-US"},"cmsTitle":"Ext Global Section - Business Travel","sectionTitle":"Business Travel","sectionDescription":"Netflix provides benefits to protect your safety and security when traveling outside of the country you work. We offer both a travel concierge service through International SOS and emergency medical coverage through the Cigna Medical Benefits Abroad plan."}]},{"sys":{"space":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"Space","id":"abx5xo923wy6"}},"id":"2p0dBoBJFaa0uqOAcaQiaO","type":"Entry","createdAt":"2019-01-09T22:27:32.860Z","updatedAt":"2020-09-24T21:37:02.980Z","environment":{"sys":{"id":"master","type":"Link","linkType":"Environment"}},"revision":5,"contentType":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"ContentType","id":"locationBasedContent"}},"locale":"en-US"},"cmsTitle":"Ext Singapore - Healt