contentType":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"ContentType","id":"sectionContent"}},"locale":"en-US"},"cmsTitle":"Ext Netherlands - Medical, Dental, Vision","sectionTitle":"Medical, Dental, Vision","sectionDescription":"Just like different content is streamed around the globe, we recognize that medical benefits work differently based on the country you live in. You may have medical offered through Netflix only, you may have a supplemental plan through Netflix that compliments a local insurance scheme, or you may have a monthly allowance to purchase benefits on your own. No matter what the case is, we make sure that you’re covered. Please review the medical plan offerings in your country.\n\nAs a Netherlands resident, you’re required to apply for healthcare insurance with a private, local insurance provider. Netflix has an agreement with an insurance company called ONVZ, who provides you with support in English. Netflix gives you a €275 tax-free allowance each month to cover your insurance costs. You can use any remaining amount to cover a partner. (Children are insured for free under their parents’ insurance until they are 18.)\nYou have the freedom to choose from the following ONVZ insurance options:\n- Basic Insurance: Standard healthcare including doctor visits, hospitalization and medication (Statutory)\n- Care Supplements: Choice of extra coverage based on your individual needs (optional)\n- Dental Supplements: Choice of dental insurance based on your individual needs (optional)\n- Travel Supplements: Possibility to cover urgent healthcare abroad while traveling on a personal note (optional)\n"},{"sys":{"space":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"Space","id":"abx5xo923wy6"}},"id":"ggdabL3Xy0ackC68QWsgu","type":"Entry","createdAt":"2018-10-25T21:18:14.061Z","updatedAt":"2020-12-28T21:08:47.309Z","environment":{"sys":{"id":"master","type":"Link","linkType":"Environment"}},"revision":4,"contentType":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"ContentType","id":"sectionContent