:"Ext India - Financial","location":{"sys":{"space":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"Space","id":"abx5xo923wy6"}},"id":"3n9U6OzG9Os4GCe4ceMg8g","type":"Entry","createdAt":"2018-08-17T17:46:22.308Z","updatedAt":"2020-11-05T16:33:14.215Z","environment":{"sys":{"id":"master","type":"Link","linkType":"Environment"}},"revision":7,"contentType":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"ContentType","id":"locationData"}},"locale":"en-US"},"cmsTitle":"India","locationName":"India","flag":{"sys":{"space":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"Space","id":"abx5xo923wy6"}},"id":"76xDoygpHysCwEcgKkK4oA","type":"Asset","createdAt":"2018-08-22T16:55:42.717Z","updatedAt":"2020-11-05T16:33:12.991Z","environment":{"sys":{"id":"master","type":"Link","linkType":"Environment"}},"revision":5,"locale":"en-US"},"title":"IN","url":"//images.ctfassets.net/abx5xo923wy6/76xDoygpHysCwEcgKkK4oA/2c6fe898b346e5864672d50d9f2b1e23/IN.svg","details":{"size":1474,"image":{"width":28,"height":20}},"fileName":"IN.svg","contentType":"image/svg+xml"},"slug":"india"},"locationSpecificContent":[{"sys":{"space":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"Space","id":"abx5xo923wy6"}},"id":"325FGHKT2MBLbAYrJucyc3","type":"Entry","createdAt":"2020-09-24T21:42:29.523Z","updatedAt":"2020-09-24T21:42:29.523Z","environment":{"sys":{"id":"master","type":"Link","linkType":"Environment"}},"revision":1,"contentType":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"ContentType","id":"sectionContent"}},"locale":"en-US"},"cmsTitle":"Ext - Global - Financial Philosophy ","sectionTitle":"Philosophy","sectionDescription":"At Netflix, we believe in top-of-personal-market compensation, providing employees the ability to save for retirement, a choice in the degree to which they participate in equity investment, and the option to make an impact on a global level by participating in our Employee Giving Program."},{"sys":{"space":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"Space","id":"abx5xo923wy6"}},"id":"2KJABq1qcMKAyYaYmeOmaO","type":"Entry","createdAt":"2018-10-26T21:43:11.809Z","updatedAt":"2019-05-23T19:13:23.340Z","environment":{"sys":{"id":"master","type":"Link","linkType":"Environment"}},"revision":3,"contentType":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"ContentType","id":"sectionContent"}},"locale":"en-US"},"cmsTitle":"Ext India Section - Retirement Pension","sectionTitle":"Retirement Pension","sectionDescription":"We help you save for retirement by contributing to the Employee Provident Fund (“EPF”) each month through payroll. Netflix will also deduct from your salary each month to satisfy your employee contribution to the EPF."},{"sys":{"space":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"Space","id":"abx5xo923wy6"}},"id":"6tTPK0lS7uSgks2eca8SwI","type":"Entry","createdAt":"2018-10-25T21:06:37.957Z","updatedAt":"2020-12-28T21:12:49.393Z","environment":{"sys":{"id":"master","type":"Link","linkType":"Environment"}},"revision":3,"contentType":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"ContentType","id":"sectionContent"}},"locale":"en-US"},"cmsTitle":"Ext Global Section - Employee Giving","sectionTitle":"Employee Giving","sectionDescription":"At Netflix, you have the ability to impact the world through the work you do. And we realize you may also want to make an impact in a more personal way. In the spirit of freedom and responsibility, you choose the organization(s) important to you, and Netflix will match your contribution $2 dollars for every $1 you donate up to $20,000 (or local currency equivalent)."},{"sys":{"space":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"Space","id":"abx5xo923wy6"}},"id":"UZSFHcRpIWM40ym28qyY4","type":"Entry","createdAt":"2018-10-31T20:31:20.889Z","updatedAt":"2021-01-20T00:36:51.938Z","environment":{"sys":{"id":"master","type":"Link","linkType":"Environment"}},"revision":15,"contentType":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"ContentType","id":"sectionGroup"}},"locale":"en-US"},"cmsTitle":"Ext Global Section - Stock Option Program (5% non-U.S.)","title":"Stock Option Program (SOP)","content":[{"sys":{"space":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"Space","id":"abx5xo923wy6"}},"id":"ILVVvWgWAuUEyyuwqoOgM","type":"Entry","createdAt":"2018-10-31T20:26:07.647Z","updatedAt":"2021-01-15T17:22:26.544Z","environment":{"sys":{"id":"master","type":"Link","linkType":"Environment"}},"revision":5,"contentType":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"ContentType","id":"sectionContent"}},"locale":"en-US"},"cmsTitle":"SOP Philosophy","sectionTitle":"Philosophy","sectionDescription":"__The Why__\nThe Netflix Stock Option Program (SOP) is unique. At Netflix, we believe in top-of-personal-market pay and providing employees with a choice in the degree to which they invest in Netflix equity through the stock option program."},{"sys":{"space":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"Space","id":"abx5xo923wy6"}},"id":"5GvXe7CyvPAxR3f1r13VE1","type":"Entry","createdAt":"2021-01-15T19:11:08.911Z","updatedAt":"2021-01-20T00:27:29.816Z","environment":{"sys":{"id":"master","type":"Link","linkType":"Environment"}},"revision":7,"contentType":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"ContentType","id":"googleVideo"}},"locale":"en-US"},"title":"Overview","googleDriveId":"19J7fdw-IzVFPDrRymU_chG977adtefNL","orientation":false,"cmsTitle":"2021 SOP Supplemental \u003e Overview Video"},{"sys":{"space":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"Space","id":"abx5xo923wy6"}},"id":"2WjR8qzsgEWswC86e06Ccw","type":"Entry","createdAt":"2018-10-31T20:34:06.975Z","updatedAt":"2021-01-15T19:00:46.116Z","environment":{"sys":{"id":"master","type":"Link","linkType":"Environment"}},"revision":9,"contentType":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"ContentType","id":"sectionContent"}},"locale":"en-US"},"cmsTitle":"SOP - Overview (Pt 1 5% External)","sectionDescription":"## The Program\nYou have the opportunity to choose the amount of cash and equity you want to receive. The stock allocation is completely voluntary. If you’d like to receive options, you can allocate as much eligible salary to the SOP as you’d like. The program allows you to benefit from the growth of our stock price over time by accumulating options and then exercising them later when the price of the underlying Netflix stock has risen. \n\u003c/br\u003e\n## What is a stock option?\nA stock option is the right to purchase a share of Netflix stock at a predetermined price, called the exercise price. Options become valuable as the stock price appreciates above the exercise price. Netflix options are granted each month and expire 10 years from the grant date. \n\nA simple way to think of a stock option is to think of it like a coupon. The coupon is valuable to you when the regular price of the item is higher than what you can buy it for with your coupon, and once they expire they are longer valid. Let’s say you receive a coupon to buy an item at $100 until the printed expiration date. You go into the store and see that the retail price is $150. You redeem your coupon and buy it for $100, which saves you $50. In the context of stock options, you might have an option with an exercise price of $100. You exercise and sell your option later on when your stock price is $150, so your gain is $50!\n"},{"sys":{"space":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"Space","id":"abx5xo923wy6"}},"id":"nAKCdbZhkWaCgUUWe02S0","type":"Entry","createdAt":"2018-09-18T01:29:50.594Z","updatedAt":"2021-01-16T02:06:13.163Z","environment":{"sys":{"id":"master","type":"Link","linkType":"Environment"}},"revision":32,"contentType":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"ContentType","id":"sectionContent"}},"locale":"en-US"},"cmsTitle":"SOP \u003e Option Grants","sectionTitle":"Option Grants","sectionDescription":"Options are granted on the first trading day of each month. The exercise price of your options will be the closing price of Netflix stock on the day that the options are granted.\n\nGenerally, there are two factors that determine the number of options you receive: \n  1) the amount you are contributing to the program and \n  2) the cost of each option. \n\nWe calculate the monthly contribution by taking the annual amount that you’ve allocated and dividing it by twelve. The cost of each option is 40% of the exercise price. We’ll divide the monthly contribution by the cost of the option,  then we know how many options you should get for the month.\n\n![(5%) Your Annual Allocation / 12](//images.ctfassets.net/abx5xo923wy6/6nvGrFnyv7rtSH2OIT2EQE/40e04d877cb8c5bb47ca74762506c77f/_5-__Your_Annual_Allocation___12.png)\n\nAs an example, assume the following:\n- Your Annual Allocation: = $12,000 annually or $1,000 monthly\n- Closing Price on the Grant Day: $200\n\nMonthly Calculation:\n![(5% SOP) $1000 / 40% x $200](//images.ctfassets.net/abx5xo923wy6/Nc3FvMKTvwCAWZZbUYyhz/e3051ca4c9ef365725a8e3cd9a7450d7/_5-_SOP___1000___40-_x__200.png)\n\nNow you have 12 options or, in other words, the right to buy 12 shares of Netflix stock at $200.\n\nA couple of points not mentioned above for simplicity's sake:\n- We don’t grant fractional options so we always round down; any remaining amount of allocation is carried over to the next month.\n- When you first join your option allocation is prorated from your hire date.\n"},{"sys":{"space":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"Space","id":"abx5xo923wy6"}},"id":"6LaqHSUAG1Kh5vYR1SkzJA","type":"Entry","createdAt":"2020-08-07T22:28:07.301Z","updatedAt":"2021-01-15T17:23:31.911Z","environment":{"sys":{"id":"master","type":"Link","linkType":"Environment"}},"revision":3,"contentType":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"ContentType","id":"sectionContent"}},"locale":"en-US"},"cmsTitle":"SOP \u003e Vest Schedule","sectionTitle":"Vest Schedule","sectionDescription":"Good news! Our options are immediately vested. This means that we can exercise our options whenever we would like, subject to insider trading restrictions."},{"sys":{"space":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"Space","id":"abx5xo923wy6"}},"id":"6pSNAGyQz5bci6QUXxCvmz","type":"Entry","createdAt":"2020-08-07T22:29:51.846Z","updatedAt":"2021-01-15T17:23:54.048Z","environment":{"sys":{"id":"master","type":"Link","linkType":"Environment"}},"revision":3,"contentType":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"ContentType","id":"sectionContent"}},"locale":"en-US"},"cmsTitle":"SOP \u003e Option Expiration","sectionTitle":"Option Expiration","sectionDescription":"Generally, your options will expire 10 years after the grant date, regardless of your employment status."},{"sys":{"space":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"Space","id":"abx5xo923wy6"}},"id":"7cNJn2CgoeQFDsjyuh4Llz","type":"Entry","createdAt":"2021-01-15T19:10:51.128Z","updatedAt":"2021-01-15T22:05:32.553Z","environment":{"sys":{"id":"master","type":"Link","linkType":"Environment"}},"revision":2,"contentType":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"ContentType","id":"sectionContent"}},"locale":"en-US"},"cmsTitle":"Supplemental SOP \u003e Understanding the Value of Your Options","sectionTitle":"Understanding the Value of Your Options","sectionDescription":"Simply put, options gain value as the stock price appreciates above the exercise price. The higher the stock price goes above the exercise price, the more your options are worth.\nParticipating in the program is an investment choice that allows you to exchange salary for options. The salary you exchange goes to cover the cost of the options, which is 40% of the exercise price. You could consider  this as the premium you pay to get the right to buy a share at the exercise price. When thinking about the actual value of the options, you want to consider this 40% cost as your initial investment. \n\nIn our example above, we exchanged $80 of our salary to get each option with a $200 exercise price. If we have exchanged $80 of salary for each option to buy a share at $200, our total investment will be $280 per share.\n\nThe stock price would need to go up to at least $280 before we start to make a profit on the salary we exchanged, which means the stock value must appreciate by at least 40% above the exercise price. Continuing our example, let us assume that we exercise and sell our 5 options at $300. If we invested $280 per option and sold at $300, our profit is $20 per option, or $100 total***.\n\n![(5% SOP) (Sell Price - (Option Cost + Exercise Price)) * Number of Options](//images.ctfassets.net/abx5xo923wy6/7aoRJj75et1XNFknt1V0UI/402f86e62e2c17df64e863b1408ad8da/_5-_SOP___Sell_Price_-__Option_Cost___Exercise_Price_____Number_of_Options.png)\n\nThis doesn’t mean that you must wait until the stock price goes up at least 40% before you exercise however. You can exercise your options at any point, as long as the stock price is above the exercise price. \n\n***To keep the math simple, the above examples do not include taxes or fees."}]}]},{"sys":{"space":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"Space","id":"abx5xo923wy6"}},"id":"5n6HsHJ2c88eCAmMWm0qiO","type":"Entry","createdAt":"2018-10-26T21:47:56.000Z","updatedAt":"2020-09-24T21:43:58.295Z","environment":{"sys":{"id":"master","type":"Link","linkType":"Environment"}},"revision":3,"contentType":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"ContentType","id":"locationBasedContent"}},"locale":"en-US"},"cmsTitle":"Ext South Korea - Financial","location":{"sys":{"space":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"Space","id":"abx5xo923wy6"}},"id":"5WSclYD8l22QIWio0KwiYI","type":"Entry","createdAt":"2018-08-17T17:47:11.059Z","updatedAt":"2020-11-05T16:33:13.551Z","environment":{"sys":{"id":"master","type":"Link","linkType":"Environment"}},"revision":8,"contentType":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"ContentType","id":"locationData"}},"locale":"en-US"},"cmsTitle":"South Korea","locationName":"South Korea","flag":{"sys":{"space":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"Space","id":"abx5xo923wy6"}},"id":"2xavtlenKEiIAe4gQMmEQw","type":"Asset","createdAt":"2018-08-22T17:00:27.487Z","updatedAt":"2020-11-05T16:33:12.978Z","environment":{"sys":{"id":"master","type":"Link","linkType":"Environment"}},"revision":5,"locale":"en-US"},"title":"KR","url":"//images.ctfassets.net/abx5xo923wy6/2xavtlenKEiIAe4gQMmEQw/858d5d761211cd0d2bfd015a520d7c5d/KR.svg","details":{"size":5056,"image":{"width":28,"height":20}},"fileName":"KR.svg","contentType":"image/svg+xml"},"slug":"south-korea"},"locationSpecificContent":[{"sys":{"space":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"Space","id":"abx5xo923wy6"}},"id":"325FGHKT2MBLbAYrJucyc3","type":"Entry","createdAt":"2020-09-24T21:42:29.523Z","updatedAt":"2020-09-24T21:42:29.523Z","environment":{"sys":{"id":"master","type":"Link","linkType":"Environment"}},"revision":1,"contentType":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"ContentType","id":"sectionContent"}},"locale":"en-US"},"cmsTitle":"Ext - Global - Financial Philosophy ","sectionTitle":"Philosophy","sectionDescription":"At Netflix, we believe in top-of-personal-market compensation, providing employees the ability to save for retirement, a choice in the degree to which they participate in equity investment, and the option to make an impact on a global level by participating in our Employee Giving Program."},{"sys":{"space":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"Space","id":"abx5xo923wy6"}},"id":"4YIIaGdovmuAIs02suKeO6","type":"Entry","createdAt":"2018-10-26T21:47:25.575Z","updatedAt":"2020-03-09T22:53:45.064Z","environment":{"sys":{"id":"master","type":"Link","linkType":"Environment"}},"revision":3,"contentType":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"ContentType","id":"sectionContent"}},"locale":"en-US"},"cmsTitle":"Ext South Korea Section - Retirement Pension","sectionTitle":"Retirement Pension","sectionDescription":"We help you save for retirement by contributing to the National Pension Scheme each month. After you’ve worked at Netflix as a full time, regular employee for one year, we’ll contribute 10% of your salary to a Defined Contribution (DC) Pension Plan on a monthly basis."},{"sys":{"space":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"Space","id":"abx5xo923wy6"}},"id":"6tTPK0lS7uSgks2eca8SwI","type":"Entry","createdAt":"2018-10-25T21:06:37.957Z","updatedAt":"2020-12-28T21:12:49.393Z","environment":{"sys":{"id":"master","type":"Link","linkType":"Environment"}},"revision":3,"contentType":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"ContentType","id":"sectionContent"}},"locale":"en-US"},"cmsTitle":"Ext Global Section - Employee Giving","sectionTitle":"Employee Giving","sectionDescription":"At Netflix, you have the ability to impact the world through the work you do. And we realize you may also want to make an impact in a more personal way. In the spirit of freedom and responsibility, you choose the organization(s) important to you, and Netflix will match your contribution $2 dollars for every $1 you donate up to $20,000 (or local currency equivalent)."},{"sys":{"space":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"Space","id":"abx5xo923wy6"}},"id":"3gvWyvt7deMUUU0m8AsymE","type":"Entry","createdAt":"2018-10-31T21:11:08.298Z","updatedAt":"2021-01-20T00:39:26.128Z","environment":{"sys":{"id":"master","type":"Link","linkType":"Environment"}},"revision":6,"contentType":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"ContentType","id":"sectionGroup"}},"locale":"en-US"},"cmsTitle":"Ext Global Group - Stock Option Program (10% no supplemental)","title":"Stock Option Program","content":[{"sys":{"space":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"Space","id":"abx5xo923wy6"}},"id":"ILVVvWgWAuUEyyuwqoOgM","type":"Entry","createdAt":"2018-10-31T20:26:07.647Z","updatedAt":"2021-01-15T17:22:26.544Z","environment":{"sys":{"id":"master","type":"Link","linkType":"Environment"}},"revision":5,"contentType":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"ContentType","id":"sectionContent"}},"locale":"en-US"},"cmsTitle":"SOP Philosophy","sectionTitle":"Philosophy","sectionDescription":"__The Why__\nThe Netflix Stock Option Program (SOP) is unique. At Netflix, we believe in top-of-personal-market pay and providing employees with a choice in the degree to which they invest in Netflix equity through the stock option program."},{"sys":{"space":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"Space","id":"abx5xo923wy6"}},"id":"1XeaFrgLKM2aaKEQMQsysm","type":"Entry","createdAt":"2018-08-22T21:58:58.616Z","updatedAt":"2021-01-16T01:52:46.232Z","environment":{"sys":{"id":"master","type":"Link","linkType":"Environment"}},"revision":16,"contentType":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"ContentType","id":"sectionContent"}},"locale":"en-US"},"cmsTitle":"SOP Non-Supplemental \u003e Overview (Pt 1 Internal and External)","sectionDescription":"## The Program\nThe SOP allows you to benefit from the growth of our stock price over time by accumulating options and then exercising them later when the price of the underlying Netflix stock has risen. If you are a salaried employee, Netflix will automatically allocate an amount equal to 5% of your annual salary to the SOP at no cost to you. During your first year at Netflix, this allocation is prorated from your hire date.\n\u003c/br\u003e\n## What is a stock option?\nA stock option is the right to purchase a share of Netflix stock at a predetermined price, called the exercise price. Options become valuable as the stock price appreciates above the exercise price. Netflix options are granted each month and expire 10 years from the grant date. \n\nA simple way to think of a stock option is to think of it like a coupon. The coupon is valuable to you when the regular price of the item is higher than what you can buy it for with your coupon, and once they expire they are longer valid. Let’s say you receive a coupon to buy an item at $100 until the printed expiration date. You go into the store and see that the retail price is $150. You redeem your coupon and buy it for $100, which saves you $50. In the context of stock options, you might have an option with an exercise price of $100. You exercise and sell your option later on when your stock price is $150, so your gain is $50!"},{"sys":{"space":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"Space","id":"abx5xo923wy6"}},"id":"2ODl1NMlS8UYGwWI0wOOGo","type":"Entry","createdAt":"2018-09-18T02:04:28.092Z","updatedAt":"2021-01-16T01:52:57.023Z","environment":{"sys":{"id":"master","type":"Link","linkType":"Environment"}},"revision":14,"contentType":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"ContentType","id":"sectionContent"}},"locale":"en-US"},"cmsTitle":"SOP Non-Supplemental \u003e Option Grants","sectionTitle":"Option Grants","sectionDescription":"Options are granted on the first trading day of each month. The exercise price of your options will be the closing price of Netflix stock on the day that the options are granted.\n\nFirst, we will determine how much Netflix is contributing to the plan for you through the Free 5%. The annual amount will be divided by 12 to get your monthly contribution. This allocation goes to cover the cost of each option, which is 40% of the exercise price. We’ll divide the monthly contribution by the cost of the option to determine how many options you should get for the month.\n\n![(10% SOP) 5% of annual salary / 12](//images.ctfassets.net/abx5xo923wy6/SVRhjbjSlfcs3pZGW7iI5/5aa47af608df08fddbf4b41321d47e92/_10-_SOP__5-_of_annual_salary___12.png)\n\nAs an example, assume the following:\n- Annual salary: 100,000\n- 5% Allocation: 5,000 annually or 416.67 monthly\n- Closing Price on the Grant Day: 200\n\nMonthly Calculation:\n![(10% SOP) 416.67 / 40% x 200](//images.ctfassets.net/abx5xo923wy6/7BzGYj7BEVZLiVrLBojo9h/0d0252427be368f32680daefc0c6b6a6/_10-_SOP__416.67___40-_x_200.png)\n\nNow you have 5 options or, in other words, the right to buy 5 shares of Netflix stock at 200.\n\nA couple of points not mentioned above for simplicity's sake: \n- We don’t grant fractional options so we always round down; any remaining amount of allocation is carried over to the next month. \n- When you first join your option allocation is prorated from your hire date."},{"sys":{"space":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"Space","id":"abx5xo923wy6"}},"id":"6LaqHSUAG1Kh5vYR1SkzJA","type":"Entry","createdAt":"2020-08-07T22:28:07.301Z","updatedAt":"2021-01-15T17:23:31.911Z","environment":{"sys":{"id":"master","type":"Link","linkType":"Environment"}},"revision":3,"contentType":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"ContentType","id":"sectionContent"}},"locale":"en-US"},"cmsTitle":"SOP \u003e Vest Schedule","sectionTitle":"Vest Schedule","sectionDescription":"Good news! Our options are immediately vested. This means that we can exercise our options whenever we would like, subject to insider trading restrictions."},{"sys":{"space":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"Space","id":"abx5xo923wy6"}},"id":"6pSNAGyQz5bci6QUXxCvmz","type":"Entry","createdAt":"2020-08-07T22:29:51.846Z","updatedAt":"2021-01-15T17:23:54.048Z","environment":{"sys":{"id":"master","type":"Link","linkType":"Environment"}},"revision":3,"contentType":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"ContentType","id":"sectionContent"}},"locale":"en-US"},"cmsTitle":"SOP \u003e Option Expiration","sectionTitle":"Option Expiration","sectionDescription":"Generally, your options will expire 10 years after the grant date, regardless of your employment status."},{"sys":{"space":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"Space","id":"abx5xo923wy6"}},"id":"2XRQ5etvAyc9dg9RU554N7","type":"Entry","createdAt":"2021-01-15T22:15:38.251Z","updatedAt":"2021-01-15T22:15:38.251Z","environment":{"sys":{"id":"master","type":"Link","linkType":"Environment"}},"revision":1,"contentType":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"ContentType","id":"sectionContent"}},"locale":"en-US"},"cmsTitle":"SOP Non-supplemental \u003e Understanding the Value of Your Options","sectionTitle":"Understanding the Value of Your Options","sectionDescription":"Before you exercise your options, you want to understand how to calculate your profit. Options are profitable when the current trading price of Netflix stock is higher than the exercise price at which it was granted to you.\n\nRemember from the example above where we were granted 5 options that had an exercise price of 200? Let’s assume you exercise those options when the market price of Netflix stock is 300. You’ll purchase each of the five shares at the exercise price of 200, sell them at 300, and make a profit of 100 for each option, or 500 total!\n\n![Value of the Free Options](//images.ctfassets.net/abx5xo923wy6/27a5P1XgXOAK8aWMG2COSI/395f275ac6eeacf669cbe58f41cae84b/ELP_Stock_Option_Program__SOP__Images.png)"}]}]},{"sys":{"space":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"Space","id":"abx5xo923wy6"}},"id":"aHUJctFpRuEm0qU8oeC28","type":"Entry","createdAt":"2018-10-26T21:49:35.644Z","updatedAt":"2020-09-24T21:44:04.747Z","environment":{"sys":{"id":"master","type":"Link","linkType":"Environment"}},"revision":3,"contentType":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"ContentType","id":"locationBasedContent"}},"locale":"en-US"},"cmsTitle":"Ext Taiwan - Financial","location":{"sys":{"space":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"Space","id":"abx5xo923wy6"}},"id":"QyuAz9rTq0aoMy2ue8ae2","type":"Entry","createdAt":"2018-08-17T17:47:23.088Z","updatedAt":"2020-11-05T16:33:13.845Z","environment":{"sys":{"id":"master","type":"Link","linkType":"Environment"}},"revision":7,"contentType":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"ContentType","id":"locationData"}},"locale":"en-US"},"cmsTitle":"Taiwan","locationName":"Taiwan","flag":{"sys":{"space":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"Space","id":"abx5xo923wy6"}},"id":"5nTssgVGViWOCICYaA8cA2","type":"Asset","createdAt":"2018-08-22T17:01:16.227Z","updatedAt":"2020-11-05T16:33:12.981Z","environment":{"sys":{"id":"master","type":"Link","linkType":"Environment"}},"revision":5,"locale":"en-US"},"title":"TW","url":"//images.ctfassets.net/abx5xo923wy6/5nTssgVGViWOCICYaA8cA2/66d8cd92ec6416a3463f4660c5ebd37a/TW.svg","details":{"size":1840,"image":{"width":28,"height":20}},"fileName":"TW.svg","contentType":"image/svg+xml"},"slug":"taiwan"},"locationSpecificContent":[{"sys":{"space":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"Space","id":"abx5xo923wy6"}},"id":"325FGHKT2MBLbAYrJucyc3","type":"Entry","createdAt":"2020-09-24T21:42:29.523Z","updatedAt":"2020-09-24T21:42:29.523Z","environment":{"sys":{"id":"master","type":"Link","linkType":"Environment"}},"revision":1,"contentType":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"ContentType","id":"sectionContent"}},"locale":"en-US"},"cmsTitle":"Ext - Global - Financial Philosophy ","sectionTitle":"Philosophy","sectionDescription":"At Netflix, we believe in top-of-personal-market compensation, providing employees the ability to save for retirement, a choice in the degree to which they participate in equity investment, and the option to make an impact on a global level by participating in our Employee Giving Program."},{"sys":{"space":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"Space","id":"abx5xo923wy6"}},"id":"6tTPK0lS7uSgks2eca8SwI","type":"Entry","createdAt":"2018-10-25T21:06:37.957Z","updatedAt":"2020-12-28T21:12:49.393Z","environment":{"sys":{"id":"master","type":"Link","linkType":"Environment"}},"revision":3,"contentType":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"ContentType","id":"sectionContent"}},"locale":"en-US"},"cmsTitle":"Ext Global Section - Employee Giving","sectionTitle":"Employee Giving","sectionDescription":"At Netflix, you have the ability to impact the world through the work you do. And we realize you may also want to make an impact in a more personal way. In the spirit of freedom and responsibility, you choose the organization(s) important to you, and Netflix will match your contribution $2 dollars for every $1 you donate up to $20,000 (or local currency equivalent)."},{"sys":{"space":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"Space","id":"abx5xo923wy6"}},"id":"3gvWyvt7deMUUU0m8AsymE","type":"Entry","createdAt":"2018-10-31T21:11:08.298Z","updatedAt":"2021-01-20T00:39:26.128Z","environment":{"sys":{"id":"master","type":"Link","linkType":"Environment"}},"revision":6,"contentType":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"ContentType","id":"sectionGroup"}},"locale":"en-US"},"cmsTitle":"Ext Global Group - Stock Option Program (10% no supplemental)","title":"Stock Option Program","content":[{"sys":{"space":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"Space","id":"abx5xo923wy6"}},"id":"ILVVvWgWAuUEyyuwqoOgM","type":"Entry","createdAt":"2018-10-31T20:26:07.647Z","updatedAt":"2021-01-15T17:22:26.544Z","environment":{"sys":{"id":"master","type":"Link","linkType":"Environment"}},"revision":5,"contentType":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"ContentType","id":"sectionContent"}},"locale":"en-US"},"cmsTitle":"SOP Philosophy","sectionTitle":"Philosophy","sectionDescription":"__The Why__\nThe Netflix Stock Option Program (SOP) is unique. At Netflix, we believe in top-of-personal-market pay and providing employees with a choice in the degree to which they invest in Netflix equity through the stock option program."},{"sys":{"space":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"Space","id":"abx5xo923wy6"}},"id":"1XeaFrgLKM2aaKEQMQsysm","type":"Entry","createdAt":"2018-08-22T21:58:58.616Z","updatedAt":"2021-01-16T01:52:46.232Z","environment":{"sys":{"id":"master","type":"Link","linkType":"Environment"}},"revision":16,"contentType":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"ContentType","id":"sectionContent"}},"locale":"en-US"},"cmsTitle":"SOP Non-Supplemental \u003e Overview (Pt 1 Internal and External)","sectionDescription":"## The Program\nThe SOP allows you to benefit from the growth of our stock price over time by accumulating options and then exercising them later when the price of the underlying Netflix stock has risen. If you are a salaried employee, Netflix will automatically allocate an amount equal to 5% of your annual salary to the SOP at no cost to you. During your first year at Netflix, this allocation is prorated from your hire date.\n\u003c/br\u003e\n## What is a stock option?\nA stock option is the right to purchase a share of Netflix stock at a predetermined price, called the exercise price. Options become valuable as the stock price appreciates above the exercise price. Netflix options are granted each month and expire 10 years from the grant date. \n\nA simple way to think of a stock option is to think of it like a coupon. The coupon is valuable to you when the regular price of the item is higher than what you can buy it for with your coupon, and once they expire they are longer valid. Let’s say you receive a coupon to buy an item at $100 until the printed expiration date. You go into the store and see that the retail price is $150. You redeem your coupon and buy it for $100, which saves you $50. In the context of stock options, you might have an option with an exercise price of $100. You exercise and sell your option later on when your stock price is $150, so your gain is $50!"},{"sys":{"space":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"Space","id":"abx5xo923wy6"}},"id":"2ODl1NMlS8UYGwWI0wOOGo","type":"Entry","createdAt":"2018-09-18T02:04:28.092Z","updatedAt":"2021-01-16T01:52:57.023Z","environment":{"sys":{"id":"master","type":"Link","linkType":"Environment"}},"revision":14,"contentType":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"ContentType","id":"sectionContent"}},"locale":"en-US"},"cmsTitle":"SOP Non-Supplemental \u003e Option Grants","sectionTitle":"Option Grants","sectionDescription":"Options are granted on the first trading day of each month. The exercise price of your options will be the closing price of Netflix stock on the day that the options are granted.\n\nFirst, we will determine how much Netflix is contributing to the plan for you through the Free 5%. The annual amount will be divided by 12 to get your monthly contribution. This allocation goes to cover the cost of each option, which is 40% of the exercise price. We’ll divide the monthly contribution by the cost of the option to determine how many options you should get for the month.\n\n![(10% SOP) 5% of annual salary / 12](//images.ctfassets.net/abx5xo923wy6/SVRhjbjSlfcs3pZGW7iI5/5aa47af608df08fddbf4b41321d47e92/_10-_SOP__5-_of_annual_salary___12.png)\n\nAs an example, assume the following:\n- Annual salary: 100,000\n- 5% Allocation: 5,000 annually or 416.67 monthly\n- Closing Price on the Grant Day: 200\n\nMonthly Calculation:\n![(10% SOP) 416.67 / 40% x 200](//images.ctfassets.net/abx5xo923wy6/7BzGYj7BEVZLiVrLBojo9h/0d0252427be368f32680daefc0c6b6a6/_10-_SOP__416.67___40-_x_200.png)\n\nNow you have 5 options or, in other words, the right to buy 5 shares of Netflix stock at 200.\n\nA couple of points not mentioned above for simplicity's sake: \n- We don’t grant fractional options so we always round down; any remaining amount of allocation is carried over to the next month. \n- When you first join your option allocation is prorated from your hire date."},{"sys":{"space":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"Space","id":"abx5xo923wy6"}},"id":"6LaqHSUAG1Kh5vYR1SkzJA","type":"Entry","createdAt":"2020-08-07T22:28:07.301Z","updatedAt":"2021-01-15T17:23:31.911Z","environment":{"sys":{"id":"master","type":"Link","linkType":"Environment"}},"revision":3,"contentType":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"ContentType","id":"sectionContent"}},"locale":"en-US"},"cmsTitle":"SOP \u003e Vest Schedule","sectionTitle":"Vest Schedule","sectionDescription":"Good news! Our options are immediately vested. This means that we can exercise our options whenever we would like, subject to insider trading restrictions."},{"sys":{"space":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"Space","id":"abx5xo923wy6"}},"id":"6pSNAGyQz5bci6QUXxCvmz","type":"Entry","createdAt":"2020-08-07T22:29:51.846Z","updatedAt":"2021-01-15T17:23:54.048Z","environment":{"sys":{"id":"master","type":"Link","linkType":"Environment"}},"revision":3,"contentType":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"ContentType","id":"sectionContent"}},"locale":"en-US"},"cmsTitle":"SOP \u003e Option Expiration","sectionTitle":"Option Expiration","sectionDescription":"Generally, your options will expire 10 years after the grant date, regardless of your employment status."},{"sys":{"space":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"Space","id":"abx5xo923wy6"}},"id":"2XRQ5etvAyc9dg9RU554N7","type":"Entry","createdAt":"2021-01-15T22:15:38.251Z","updatedAt":"2021-01-15T22:15:38.251Z","environment":{"sys":{"id":"master","type":"Link","linkType":"Environment"}},"revision":1,"contentType":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"ContentType","id":"sectionContent"}},"locale":"en-US"},"cmsTitle":"SOP Non-supplemental \u003e Understanding the Value of Your Options","sectionTitle":"Understanding the Value of Your Options","sectionDescription":"Before you exercise your options, you want to understand how to calculate your profit. Options are profitable when the current trading price of Netflix stock is higher than the exercise price at which it was granted to you.\n\nRemember from the example above where we were granted 5 options that had an exercise price of 200? Let’s assume you exercise those options when the market price of Netflix stock is 300. You’ll purchase each of the five shares at the exercise price of 200, sell them at 300, and make a profit of 100 for each option, or 500 total!\n\n![Value of the Free Options](//images.ctfassets.net/abx5xo923wy6/27a5P1XgXOAK8aWMG2COSI/395f275ac6eeacf669cbe58f41cae84b/ELP_Stock_Option_Program__SOP__Images.png)"}]}]},{"sys":{"space":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"Space","id":"abx5xo923wy6"}},"id":"4XFpPIIJWgo0C2uOm6866A","type":"Entry","createdAt":"2018-10-26T21:58:33.939Z","updatedAt":"2020-09-24T21:44:10.347Z","environment":{"sys":{"id":"master","type":"Link","linkType":"Environment"}},"revision":3,"contentType":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"ContentType","id":"locationBasedContent"}},"locale":"en-US"},"cmsTitle":"Ext United Kingdom - Financial","location":{"sys":{"space":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"Space","id":"abx5xo923wy6"}},"id":"6iVpjh6MuW4WGQY6cAWSsc","type":"Entry","createdAt":"2018-08-17T17:47:45.557Z","updatedAt":"2020-11-05T16:33:15.563Z","environment":{"sys":{"id":"master","type":"Link","linkType":"Environment"}},"revision":7,"contentType":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"ContentType","id":"locationData"}},"locale":"en-US"},"cmsTitle":"United Kingdom","locationName":"United Kingdom","flag":{"sys":{"space":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"Space","id":"abx5xo923wy6"}},"id":"SZeSiuzXIyWyGUIOu8KIE","type":"Asset","createdAt":"2018-08-22T17:02:07.793Z","updatedAt":"2020-11-05T16:33:13.029Z","environment":{"sys":{"id":"master","type":"Link","linkType":"Environment"}},"revision":5,"locale":"en-US"},"title":"GB","url":"//images.ctfassets.net/abx5xo923wy6/SZeSiuzXIyWyGUIOu8KIE/a84cb018f501db6f464a84bc19efa656/GB.svg","details":{"size":2740,"image":{"width":28,"height":20}},"fileName":"GB.svg","contentType":"image/svg+xml"},"slug":"united-kingdom"},"locationSpecificContent":[{"sys":{"space":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"Space","id":"abx5xo923wy6"}},"id":"325FGHKT2MBLbAYrJucyc3","type":"Entry","createdAt":"2020-09-24T21:42:29.523Z","updatedAt":"2020-09-24T21:42:29.523Z","environment":{"sys":{"id":"master","type":"Link","linkType":"Environment"}},"revision":1,"contentType":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"ContentType","id":"sectionContent"}},"locale":"en-US"},"cmsTitle":"Ext - Global - Financial Philosophy ","sectionTitle":"Philosophy","sectionDescription":"At Netflix, we believe in top-of-personal-market compensation, providing employees the ability to save for retirement, a choice in the degree to which they participate in equity investment, and the option to make an impact on a global level by participating in our Employee Giving Program."},{"sys":{"space":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"Space","id":"abx5xo923wy6"}},"id":"csZ6ED5Lck0MyqGs864Q","type":"Entry","createdAt":"2018-10-26T21:58:25.529Z","updatedAt":"2020-11-03T19:19:40.655Z","environment":{"sys":{"id":"master","type":"Link","linkType":"Environment"}},"revision":4,"contentType":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"ContentType","id":"sectionContent"}},"locale":"en-US"},"cmsTitle":"Ext UK Section - Retirement Pension","sectionTitle":"Retirement Pension","sectionDescription":"We help you save for retirement by matching your contributions, up to 7% of your monthly salary, to a retirement pension plan through Scottish Widows."},{"sys":{"space":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"Space","id":"abx5xo923wy6"}},"id":"6tTPK0lS7uSgks2eca8SwI","type":"Entry","createdAt":"2018-10-25T21:06:37.957Z","updatedAt":"2020-12-28T21:12:49.393Z","environment":{"sys":{"id":"master","type":"Link","linkType":"Environment"}},"revision":3,"contentType":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"ContentType","id":"sectionContent"}},"locale":"en-US"},"cmsTitle":"Ext Global Section - Employee Giving","sectionTitle":"Employee Giving","sectionDescription":"At Netflix, you have the ability to impact the world through the work you do. And we realize you may also want to make an impact in a more personal way. In the spirit of freedom and responsibility, you choose the organization(s) important to you, and Netflix will match your contribution $2 dollars for every $1 you donate up to $20,000 (or local currency equivalent)."},{"sys":{"space":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"Space","id":"abx5xo923wy6"}},"id":"UZSFHcRpIWM40ym28qyY4","type":"Entry","createdAt":"2018-10-31T20:31:20.889Z","updatedAt":"2021-01-20T00:36:51.938Z","environment":{"sys":{"id":"master","type":"Link","linkType":"Environment"}},"revision":15,"contentType":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"ContentType","id":"sectionGroup"}},"locale":"en-US"},"cmsTitle":"Ext Global Section - Stock Option Program (5% non-U.S.)","title":"Stock Option Program (SOP)","content":[{"sys":{"space":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"Space","id":"abx5xo923wy6"}},"id":"ILVVvWgWAuUEyyuwqoOgM","type":"Entry","createdAt":"2018-10-31T20:26:07.647Z","updatedAt":"2021-01-15T17:22:26.544Z","environment":{"sys":{"id":"master","type":"Link","linkType":"Environment"}},"revision":5,"contentType":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"ContentType","id":"sectionContent"}},"locale":"en-US"},"cmsTitle":"SOP Philosophy","sectionTitle":"Philosophy","sectionDescription":"__The Why__\nThe Netflix Stock Option Program (SOP) is unique. At Netflix, we believe in top-of-personal-market pay and providing employees with a choice in the degree to which they invest in Netflix equity through the stock option program."},{"sys":{"space":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"Space","id":"abx5xo923wy6"}},"id":"5GvXe7CyvPAxR3f1r13VE1","type":"Entry","createdAt":"2021-01-15T19:11:08.911Z","updatedAt":"2021-01-20T00:27:29.816Z","environment":{"sys":{"id":"master","type":"Link","linkType":"Environment"}},"revision":7,"contentType":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"ContentType","id":"googleVideo"}},"locale":"en-US"},"title":"Overview","googleDriveId":"19J7fdw-IzVFPDrRymU_chG977adtefNL","orientation":false,"cmsTitle":"2021 SOP Supplemental \u003e Overview Video"},{"sys":{"space":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"Space","id":"abx5xo923wy6"}},"id":"2WjR8qzsgEWswC86e06Ccw","type":"Entry","createdAt":"2018-10-31T20:34:06.975Z","updatedAt":"2021-01-15T19:00:46.116Z","environment":{"sys":{"id":"master","type":"Link","linkType":"Environment"}},"revision":9,"contentType":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"ContentType","id":"sectionContent"}},"locale":"en-US"},"cmsTitle":"SOP - Overview (Pt 1 5% External)","sectionDescription":"## The Program\nYou have the opportunity to choose the amount of cash and equity you want to receive. The stock allocation is completely voluntary. If you’d like to receive options, you can allocate as much eligible salary to the SOP as you’d like. The program allows you to benefit from the growth of our stock price over time by accumulating options and then exercising them later when the price of the underlying Netflix stock has risen. \n\u003c/br\u003e\n## What is a stock option?\nA stock option is the right to purchase a share of Netflix stock at a predetermined price, called the exercise price. Options become valuable as the stock price appreciates above the exercise price. Netflix options are granted each month and expire 10 years from the grant date. \n\nA simple way to think of a stock option is to think of it like a coupon. The coupon is valuable to you when the regular price of the item is higher than what you can buy it for with your coupon, and once they expire they are longer valid. Let’s say you receive a coupon to buy an item at $100 until the printed expiration date. You go into the store and see that the retail price is $150. You redeem your coupon and buy it for $100, which saves you $50. In the context of stock options, you might have an option with an exercise price of $100. You exercise and sell your option later on when your stock price is $150, so your gain is $50!\n"},{"sys":{"space":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"Space","id":"abx5xo923wy6"}},"id":"nAKCdbZhkWaCgUUWe02S0","type":"Entry","createdAt":"2018-09-18T01:29:50.594Z","updatedAt":"2021-01-16T02:06:13.163Z","environment":{"sys":{"id":"master","type":"Link","linkType":"Environment"}},"revision":32,"contentType":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"ContentType","id":"sectionContent"}},"locale":"en-US"},"cmsTitle":"SOP \u003e Option Grants","sectionTitle":"Option Grants","sectionDescription":"Options are granted on the first trading day of each month. The exercise price of your options will be the closing price of Netflix stock on the day that the options are granted.\n\nGenerally, there are two factors that determine the number of options you receive: \n  1) the amount you are contributing to the program and \n  2) the cost of each option. \n\nWe calculate the monthly contribution by taking the annual amount that you’ve allocated and dividing it by twelve. The cost of each option is 40% of the exercise price. We’ll divide the monthly contribution by the cost of the option,  then we know how many options you should get for the month.\n\n![(5%) Your Annual Allocation / 12](//images.ctfassets.net/abx5xo923wy6/6nvGrFnyv7rtSH2OIT2EQE/40e04d877cb8c5bb47ca74762506c77f/_5-__Your_Annual_Allocation___12.png)\n\nAs an example, assume the following:\n- Your Annual Allocation: = $12,000 annually or $1,000 monthly\n- Closing Price on the Grant Day: $200\n\nMonthly Calculation:\n![(5% SOP) $1000 / 40% x $200](//images.ctfassets.net/abx5xo923wy6/Nc3FvMKTvwCAWZZbUYyhz/e3051ca4c9ef365725a8e3cd9a7450d7/_5-_SOP___1000___40-_x__200.png)\n\nNow you have 12 options or, in other words, the right to buy 12 shares of Netflix stock at $200.\n\nA couple of points not mentioned above for simplicity's sake:\n- We don’t grant fractional options so we always round down; any remaining amount of allocation is carried over to the next month.\n- When you first join your option allocation is prorated from your hire date.\n"},{"sys":{"space":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"Space","id":"abx5xo923wy6"}},"id":"6LaqHSUAG1Kh5vYR1SkzJA","type":"Entry","createdAt":"2020-08-07T22:28:07.301Z","updatedAt":"2021-01-15T17:23:31.911Z","environment":{"sys":{"id":"master","type":"Link","linkType":"Environment"}},"revision":3,"contentType":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"ContentType","id":"sectionContent"}},"locale":"en-US"},"cmsTitle":"SOP \u003e Vest Schedule","sectionTitle":"Vest Schedule","sectionDescription":"Good news! Our options are immediately vested. This means that we can exercise our options whenever we would like, subject to insider trading restrictions."},{"sys":{"space":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"Space","id":"abx5xo923wy6"}},"id":"6pSNAGyQz5bci6QUXxCvmz","type":"Entry","createdAt":"2020-08-07T22:29:51.846Z","updatedAt":"2021-01-15T17:23:54.048Z","environment":{"sys":{"id":"master","type":"Link","linkType":"Environment"}},"revision":3,"contentType":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"ContentType","id":"sectionContent"}},"locale":"en-US"},"cmsTitle":"SOP \u003e Option Expiration","sectionTitle":"Option Expiration","sectionDescription":"Generally, your options will expire 10 years after the grant date, regardless of your employment status."},{"sys":{"space":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"Space","id":"abx5xo923wy6"}},"id":"7cNJn2CgoeQFDsjyuh4Llz","type":"Entry","createdAt":"2021-01-15T19:10:51.128Z","updatedAt":"2021-01-15T22:05:32.553Z","environment":{"sys":{"id":"master","type":"Link","linkType":"Environment"}},"revision":2,"contentType":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"ContentType","id":"sectionContent"}},"locale":"en-US"},"cmsTitle":"Supplemental SOP \u003e Understanding the Value of Your Options","sectionTitle":"Understanding the Value of Your Options","sectionDescription":"Simply put, options gain value as the stock price appreciates above the exercise price. The higher the stock price goes above the exercise price, the more your options are worth.\nParticipating in the program is an investment choice that allows you to exchange salary for options. The salary you exchange goes to cover the cost of the options, which is 40% of the exercise price. You could consider  this as the premium you pay to get the right to buy a share at the exercise price. When thinking about the actual value of the options, you want to consider this 40% cost as your initial investment. \n\nIn our example above, we exchanged $80 of our salary to get each option with a $200 exercise price. If we have exchanged $80 of salary for each option to buy a share at $200, our total investment will be $280 per share.\n\nThe stock price would need to go up to at least $280 before we start to make a profit on the salary we exchanged, which means the stock value must appreciate by at least 40% above the exercise price. Continuing our example, let us assume that we exercise and sell our 5 options at $300. If we invested $280 per option and sold at $300, our profit is $20 per option, or $100 total***.\n\n![(5% SOP) (Sell Price - (Option Cost + Exercise Price)) * Number of Options](//images.ctfassets.net/abx5xo923wy6/7aoRJj75et1XNFknt1V0UI/402f86e62e2c17df64e863b1408ad8da/_5-_SOP___Sell_Price_-__Option_Cost___Exercise_Price_____Number_of_Options.png)\n\nThis doesn’t mean that you must wait until the stock price goes up at least 40% before you exercise however. You can exercise your options at any point, as long as the stock price is above the exercise price. \n\n***To keep the math simple, the above examples do not include taxes or fees."}]}]},{"sys":{"space":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"Space","id":"abx5xo923wy6"}},"id":"17IKZSlTKQoWAOSYo8kIo2","type":"Entry","createdAt":"2018-10-26T21:59:53.117Z","updatedAt":"2020-09-24T21:44:15.807Z","environment":{"sys":{"id":"master","type":"Link","linkType":"Environment"}},"revision":5,"contentType":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"ContentType","id":"locationBasedContent"}},"locale":"en-US"},"cmsTitle":"Ext Spain - Financial","location":{"sys":{"space":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"Space","id":"abx5xo923wy6"}},"id":"4OhtqM7Q8U4OisaAeyEgOE","type":"Entry","createdAt":"2018-08-28T17:57:45.091Z","updatedAt":"2020-11-05T16:33:15.671Z","environment":{"sys":{"id":"master","type":"Link","linkType":"Environment"}},"revision":6,"contentType":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"ContentType","id":"locationData"}},"locale":"en-US"},"cmsTitle":"Spain","locationName":"Spain","flag":{"sys":{"space":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"Space","id":"abx5xo923wy6"}},"id":"1LcmiG8D6IQO8ow2YkU8","type":"Asset","createdAt":"2018-08-28T18:02:21.841Z","updatedAt":"2020-11-05T16:33:13.032Z","environment":{"sys":{"id":"master","type":"Link","linkType":"Environment"}},"revision":6,"locale":"en-US"},"title":"es","url":"//images.ctfassets.net/abx5xo923wy6/1LcmiG8D6IQO8ow2YkU8/7db72e9b3cb6c9fc7bf2bb0b6fec8ae6/ES.svg","details":{"size":2780,"image":{"width":28,"height":20}},"fileName":"ES.svg","contentType":"image/svg+xml"},"slug":"spain"},"locationSpecificContent":[{"sys":{"space":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"Space","id":"abx5xo923wy6"}},"id":"325FGHKT2MBLbAYrJucyc3","type":"Entry","createdAt":"2020-09-24T21:42:29.523Z","updatedAt":"2020-09-24T21:42:29.523Z","environment":{"sys":{"id":"master","type":"Link","linkType":"Environment"}},"revision":1,"contentType":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"ContentType","id":"sectionContent"}},"locale":"en-US"},"cmsTitle":"Ext - Global - Financial Philosophy ","sectionTitle":"Philosophy","sectionDescription":"At Netflix, we believe in top-of-personal-market compensation, providing employees the ability to save for retirement, a choice in the degree to which they participate in equity investment, and the option to make an impact on a global level by participating in our Employee Giving Program."},{"sys":{"space":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"Space","id":"abx5xo923wy6"}},"id":"4hEwG4wED6M2oio4oi406i","type":"Entry","createdAt":"2018-10-30T21:32:14.933Z","updatedAt":"2019-02-04T17:54:25.391Z","environment":{"sys":{"id":"master","type":"Link","linkType":"Environment"}},"revision":2,"contentType":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"ContentType","id":"sectionContent"}},"locale":"en-US"},"cmsTitle":"Ext Spain Section - Retirement Pension","sectionTitle":"Retirement Pension","sectionDescription":"Netflix offers a Defined Contribution (DC) retirement plan through Allianz. You can contribute between 0.5% - 2.5% of your pensionable salary. Netflix will contribute 2x your contribution. "},{"sys":{"space":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"Space","id":"abx5xo923wy6"}},"id":"6tTPK0lS7uSgks2eca8SwI","type":"Entry","createdAt":"2018-10-25T21:06:37.957Z","updatedAt":"2020-12-28T21:12:49.393Z","environment":{"sys":{"id":"master","type":"Link","linkType":"Environment"}},"revision":3,"contentType":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"ContentType","id":"sectionContent"}},"locale":"en-US"},"cmsTitle":"Ext Global Section - Employee Giving","sectionTitle":"Employee Giving","sectionDescription":"At Netflix, you have the ability to impact the world through the work you do. And we realize you may also want to make an impact in a more personal way. In the spirit of freedom and responsibility, you choose the organization(s) important to you, and Netflix will match your contribution $2 dollars for every $1 you donate up to $20,000 (or local currency equivalent)."},{"sys":{"space":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"Space","id":"abx5xo923wy6"}},"id":"UZSFHcRpIWM40ym28qyY4","type":"Entry","createdAt":"2018-10-31T20:31:20.889Z","updatedAt":"2021-01-20T00:36:51.938Z","environment":{"sys":{"id":"master","type":"Link","linkType":"Environment"}},"revision":15,"contentType":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"ContentType","id":"sectionGroup"}},"locale":"en-US"},"cmsTitle":"Ext Global Section - Stock Option Program (5% non-U.S.)","title":"Stock Option Program (SOP)","content":[{"sys":{"space":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"Space","id":"abx5xo923wy6"}},"id":"ILVVvWgWAuUEyyuwqoOgM","type":"Entry","createdAt":"2018-10-31T20:26:07.647Z","updatedAt":"2021-01-15T17:22:26.544Z","environment":{"sys":{"id":"master","type":"Link","linkType":"Environment"}},"revision":5,"contentType":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"ContentType","id":"sectionContent"}},"locale":"en-US"},"cmsTitle":"SOP Philosophy","sectionTitle":"Philosophy","sectionDescription":"__The Why__\nThe Netflix Stock Option Program (SOP) is unique. At Netflix, we believe in top-of-personal-market pay and providing employees with a choice in the degree to which they invest in Netflix equity through the stock option program."},{"sys":{"space":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"Space","id":"abx5xo923wy6"}},"id":"5GvXe7CyvPAxR3f1r13VE1","type":"Entry","createdAt":"2021-01-15T19:11:08.911Z","updatedAt":"2021-01-20T00:27:29.816Z","environment":{"sys":{"id":"master","type":"Link","linkType":"Environment"}},"revision":7,"contentType":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"ContentType","id":"googleVideo"}},"locale":"en-US"},"title":"Overview","googleDriveId":"19J7fdw-IzVFPDrRymU_chG977adtefNL","orientation":false,"cmsTitle":"2021 SOP Supplemental \u003e Overview Video"},{"sys":{"space":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"Space","id":"abx5xo923wy6"}},"id":"2WjR8qzsgEWswC86e06Ccw","type":"Entry","createdAt":"2018-10-31T20:34:06.975Z","updatedAt":"2021-01-15T19:00:46.116Z","environment":{"sys":{"id":"master","type":"Link","linkType":"Environment"}},"revision":9,"contentType":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"ContentType","id":"sectionContent"}},"locale":"en-US"},"cmsTitle":"SOP - Overview (Pt 1 5% External)","sectionDescription":"## The Program\nYou have the opportunity to choose the amount of cash and equity you want to receive. The stock allocation is completely voluntary. If you’d like to receive options, you can allocate as much eligible salary to the SOP as you’d like. The program allows you to benefit from the growth of our stock price over time by accumulating options and then exercising them later when the price of the underlying Netflix stock has risen. \n\u003c/br\u003e\n## What is a stock option?\nA stock option is the right to purchase a share of Netflix stock at a predetermined price, called the exercise price. Options become valuable as the stock price appreciates above the exercise price. Netflix options are granted each month and expire 10 years from the grant date. \n\nA simple way to think of a stock option is to think of it like a coupon. The coupon is valuable to you when the regular price of the item is higher than what you can buy it for with your coupon, and once they expire they are longer valid. Let’s say you receive a coupon to buy an item at $100 until the printed expiration date. You go into the store and see that the retail price is $150. You redeem your coupon and buy it for $100, which saves you $50. In the context of stock options, you might have an option with an exercise price of $100. You exercise and sell your option later on when your stock price is $150, so your gain is $50!\n"},{"sys":{"space":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"Space","id":"abx5xo923wy6"}},"id":"nAKCdbZhkWaCgUUWe02S0","type":"Entry","createdAt":"2018-09-18T01:29:50.594Z","updatedAt":"2021-01-16T02:06:13.163Z","environment":{"sys":{"id":"master","type":"Link","linkType":"Environment"}},"revision":32,"contentType":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"ContentType","id":"sectionContent"}},"locale":"en-US"},"cmsTitle":"SOP \u003e Option Grants","sectionTitle":"Option Grants","sectionDescription":"Options are granted on the first trading day of each month. The exercise price of your options will be the closing price of Netflix stock on the day that the options are granted.\n\nGenerally, there are two factors that determine the number of options you receive: \n  1) the amount you are contributing to the program and \n  2) the cost of each option. \n\nWe calculate the monthly contribution by taking the annual amount that you’ve allocated and dividing it by twelve. The cost of each option is 40% of the exercise price. We’ll divide the monthly contribution by the cost of the option,  then we know how many options you should get for the month.\n\n![(5%) Your Annual Allocation / 12](//images.ctfassets.net/abx5xo923wy6/6nvGrFnyv7rtSH2OIT2EQE/40e04d877cb8c5bb47ca74762506c77f/_5-__Your_Annual_Allocation___12.png)\n\nAs an example, assume the following:\n- Your Annual Allocation: = $12,000 annually or $1,000 monthly\n- Closing Price on the Grant Day: $200\n\nMonthly Calculation:\n![(5% SOP) $1000 / 40% x $200](//images.ctfassets.net/abx5xo923wy6/Nc3FvMKTvwCAWZZbUYyhz/e3051ca4c9ef365725a8e3cd9a7450d7/_5-_SOP___1000___40-_x__200.png)\n\nNow you have 12 options or, in other words, the right to buy 12 shares of Netflix stock at $200.\n\nA couple of points not mentioned above for simplicity's sake:\n- We don’t grant fractional options so we always round down; any remaining amount of allocation is carried over to the next month.\n- When you first join your option allocation is prorated from your hire date.\n"},{"sys":{"space":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"Space","id":"abx5xo923wy6"}},"id":"6LaqHSUAG1Kh5vYR1SkzJA","type":"Entry","createdAt":"2020-08-07T22:28:07.301Z","updatedAt":"2021-01-15T17:23:31.911Z","environment":{"sys":{"id":"master","type":"Link","linkType":"Environment"}},"revision":3,"contentType":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"ContentType","id":"sectionContent"}},"locale":"en-US"},"cmsTitle":"SOP \u003e Vest Schedule","sectionTitle":"Vest Schedule","sectionDescription":"Good news! Our options are immediately vested. This means that we can exercise our options whenever we would like, subject to insider trading restrictions."},{"sys":{"space":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"Space","id":"abx5xo923wy6"}},"id":"6pSNAGyQz5bci6QUXxCvmz","type":"Entry","createdAt":"2020-08-07T22:29:51.846Z","updatedAt":"2021-01-15T17:23:54.048Z","environment":{"sys":{"id":"master","type":"Link","linkType":"Environment"}},"revision":3,"contentType":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"ContentType","id":"sectionContent"}},"locale":"en-US"},"cmsTitle":"SOP \u003e Option Expiration","sectionTitle":"Option Expiration","sectionDescription":"Generally, your options will expire 10 years after the grant date, regardless of your employment status."},{"sys":{"space":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"Space","id":"abx5xo923wy6"}},"id":"7cNJn2CgoeQFDsjyuh4Llz","type":"Entry","createdAt":"2021-01-15T19:10:51.128Z","updatedAt":"2021-01-15T22:05:32.553Z","environment":{"sys":{"id":"master","type":"Link","linkType":"Environment"}},"revision":2,"contentType":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"ContentType","id":"sectionContent"}},"locale":"en-US"},"cmsTitle":"Supplemental SOP \u003e Understanding the Value of Your Options","sectionTitle":"Understanding the Value of Your Options","sectionDescription":"Simply put, options gain value as the stock price appreciates above the exercise price. The higher the stock price goes above the exercise price, the more your options are worth.\nParticipating in the program is an investment choice that allows you to exchange salary for options. The salary you exchange goes to cover the cost of the options, which is 40% of the exercise price. You could consider  this as the premium you pay to get the right to buy a share at the exercise price. When thinking about the actual value of the options, you want to consider this 40% cost as your initial investment. \n\nIn our example above, we exchanged $80 of our salary to get each option with a $200 exercise price. If we have exchanged $80 of salary for each option to buy a share at $200, our total investment will be $280 per share.\n\nThe stock price would need to go up to at least $280 before we start to make a profit on the salary we exchanged, which means the stock value must appreciate by at least 40% above the exercise price. Continuing our example, let us assume that we exercise and sell our 5 options at $300. If we invested $280 per option and sold at $300, our profit is $20 per option, or $100 total***.\n\n![(5% SOP) (Sell Price - (Option Cost + Exercise Price)) * Number of Options](//images.ctfassets.net/abx5xo923wy6/7aoRJj75et1XNFknt1V0UI/402f86e62e2c17df64e863b1408ad8da/_5-_SOP___Sell_Price_-__Option_Cost___Exercise_Price_____Number_of_Options.png)\n\nThis doesn’t mean that you must wait until the stock price goes up at least 40% before you exercise however. You can exercise your options at any point, as long as the stock price is above the exercise price. \n\n***To keep the math simple, the above examples do not include taxes or fees."}]}]},{"sys":{"space":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"Space","id":"abx5xo923wy6"}},"id":"61WgtRdsCQ2S2qaOaKamMU","type":"Entry","createdAt":"2018-11-06T00:20:21.821Z","updatedAt":"2020-10-12T21:08:53.633Z","environment":{"sys":{"id":"master","type":"Link","linkType":"Environment"}},"revision":4,"contentType":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"ContentType","id":"locationBasedContent"}},"locale":"en-US"},"cmsTitle":"Ext France - Financial","location":{"sys":{"space":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"Space","id":"abx5xo923wy6"}},"id":"25TQNhqX4UWUg0KssIASoI","type":"Entry","createdAt":"2018-08-28T17:51:08.663Z","updatedAt":"2020-11-05T16:33:15.760Z","environment":{"sys":{"id":"master","type":"Link","linkType":"Environment"}},"revision":8,"contentType":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"ContentType","id":"locationData"}},"locale":"en-US"},"cmsTitle":"France","locationName":"France","flag":{"sys":{"space":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"Space","id":"abx5xo923wy6"}},"id":"6y7gVx4MqQEwemkWgkequI","type":"Asset","createdAt":"2018-08-28T18:03:20.383Z","updatedAt":"2020-11-05T16:33:13.036Z","environment":{"sys":{"id":"master","type":"Link","linkType":"Environment"}},"revision":8,"locale":"en-US"},"title":"fr","url":"//images.ctfassets.net/abx5xo923wy6/6y7gVx4MqQEwemkWgkequI/729c3a71ea97fb3a9355dbc41f8c35da/FR.svg","details":{"size":1188,"image":{"width":28,"height":20}},"fileName":"FR.svg","contentType":"image/svg+xml"},"slug":"france"},"locationSpecificContent":[{"sys":{"space":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"Space","id":"abx5xo923wy6"}},"id":"325FGHKT2MBLbAYrJucyc3","type":"Entry","createdAt":"2020-09-24T21:42:29.523Z","updatedAt":"2020-09-24T21:42:29.523Z","environment":{"sys":{"id":"master","type":"Link","linkType":"Environment"}},"revision":1,"contentType":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"ContentType","id":"sectionContent"}},"locale":"en-US"},"cmsTitle":"Ext - Global - Financial Philosophy ","sectionTitle":"Philosophy","sectionDescription":"At Netflix, we believe in top-of-personal-market compensation, providing employees the ability to save for retirement, a choice in the degree to which they participate in equity investment, and the option to make an impact on a global level by participating in our Employee Giving Program."},{"sys":{"space":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"Space","id":"abx5xo923wy6"}},"id":"789vdHYUrSwQGMM6MAYsmS","type":"Entry","createdAt":"2018-11-06T00:19:20.736Z","updatedAt":"2020-09-24T21:44:42.341Z","environment":{"sys":{"id":"master","type":"Link","linkType":"Environment"}},"revision":3,"contentType":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"ContentType","id":"sectionContent"}},"locale":"en-US"},"cmsTitle":"Ext France Section - Retirement Pension","sectionTitle":"Retirement Pension ","sectionDescription":"Netflix offers a Defined Contribution plan through AXA. Netflix will contribute 4% of your salary to the retirement plan. "},{"sys":{"space":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"Space","id":"abx5xo923wy6"}},"id":"6tTPK0lS7uSgks2eca8SwI","type":"Entry","createdAt":"2018-10-25T21:06:37.957Z","updatedAt":"2020-12-28T21:12:49.393Z","environment":{"sys":{"id":"master","type":"Link","linkType":"Environment"}},"revision":3,"contentType":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"ContentType","id":"sectionContent"}},"locale":"en-US"},"cmsTitle":"Ext Global Section - Employee Giving","sectionTitle":"Employee Giving","sectionDescription":"At Netflix, you have the ability to impact the world through the work you do. And we realize you may also want to make an impact in a more personal way. In the spirit of freedom and responsibility, you choose the organization(s) important to you, and Netflix will match your contribution $2 dollars for every $1 you donate up to $20,000 (or local currency equivalent)."},{"sys":{"space":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"Space","id":"abx5xo923wy6"}},"id":"3gvWyvt7deMUUU0m8AsymE","type":"Entry","createdAt":"2018-10-31T21:11:08.298Z","updatedAt":"2021-01-20T00:39:26.128Z","environment":{"sys":{"id":"master","type":"Link","linkType":"Environment"}},"revision":6,"contentType":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"ContentType","id":"sectionGroup"}},"locale":"en-US"},"cmsTitle":"Ext Global Group - Stock Option Program (10% no supplemental)","title":"Stock Option Program","content":[{"sys":{"space":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"Space","id":"abx5xo923wy6"}},"id":"ILVVvWgWAuUEyyuwqoOgM","type":"Entry","createdAt":"2018-10-31T20:26:07.647Z","updatedAt":"2021-01-15T17:22:26.544Z","environment":{"sys":{"id":"master","type":"Link","linkType":"Environment"}},"revision":5,"contentType":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"ContentType","id":"sectionContent"}},"locale":"en-US"},"cmsTitle":"SOP Philosophy","sectionTitle":"Philosophy","sectionDescription":"__The Why__\nThe Netflix Stock Option Program (SOP) is unique. At Netflix, we believe in top-of-personal-market pay and providing employees with a choice in the degree to which they invest in Netflix equity through the stock option program."},{"sys":{"space":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"Space","id":"abx5xo923wy6"}},"id":"1XeaFrgLKM2aaKEQMQsysm","type":"Entry","createdAt":"2018-08-22T21:58:58.616Z","updatedAt":"2021-01-16T01:52:46.232Z","environment":{"sys":{"id":"master","type":"Link","linkType":"Environment"}},"revision":16,"contentType":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"ContentType","id":"sectionContent"}},"locale":"en-US"},"cmsTitle":"SOP Non-Supplemental \u003e Overview (Pt 1 Internal and External)","sectionDescription":"## The Program\nThe SOP allows you to benefit from the growth of our stock price over time by accumulating options and then exercising them later when the price of the underlying Netflix stock has risen. If you are a salaried employee, Netflix will automatically allocate an amount equal to 5% of your annual salary to the SOP at no cost to you. During your first year at Netflix, this allocation is prorated from your hire date.\n\u003c/br\u003e\n## What is a stock option?\nA stock option is the right to purchase a share of Netflix stock at a predetermined price, called the exercise price. Options become valuable as the stock price appreciates above the exercise price. Netflix options are granted each month and expire 10 years from the grant date. \n\nA simple way to think of a stock option is to think of it like a coupon. The coupon is valuable to you when the regular price of the item is higher than what you can buy it for with your coupon, and once they expire they are longer valid. Let’s say you receive a coupon to buy an item at $100 until the printed expiration date. You go into the store and see that the retail price is $150. You redeem your coupon and buy it for $100, which saves you $50. In the context of stock options, you might have an option with an exercise price of $100. You exercise and sell your option later on when your stock price is $150, so your gain is $50!"},{"sys":{"space":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"Space","id":"abx5xo923wy6"}},"id":"2ODl1NMlS8UYGwWI0wOOGo","type":"Entry","createdAt":"2018-09-18T02:04:28.092Z","updatedAt":"2021-01-16T01:52:57.023Z","environment":{"sys":{"id":"master","type":"Link","linkType":"Environment"}},"revision":14,"contentType":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"ContentType","id":"sectionContent"}},"locale":"en-US"},"cmsTitle":"SOP Non-Supplemental \u003e Option Grants","sectionTitle":"Option Grants","sectionDescription":"Options are granted on the first trading day of each month. The exercise price of your options will be the closing price of Netflix stock on the day that the options are granted.\n\nFirst, we will determine how much Netflix is contributing to the plan for you through the Free 5%. The annual amount will be divided by 12 to get your monthly contribution. This allocation goes to cover the cost of each option, which is 40% of the exercise price. We’ll divide the monthly contribution by the cost of the option to determine how many options you should get for the month.\n\n![(10% SOP) 5% of annual salary / 12](//images.ctfassets.net/abx5xo923wy6/SVRhjbjSlfcs3pZGW7iI5/5aa47af608df08fddbf4b41321d47e92/_10-_SOP__5-_of_annual_salary___12.png)\n\nAs an example, assume the following:\n- Annual salary: 100,000\n- 5% Allocation: 5,000 annually or 416.67 monthly\n- Closing Price on the Grant Day: 200\n\nMonthly Calculation:\n![(10% SOP) 416.67 / 40% x 200](//images.ctfassets.net/abx5xo923wy6/7BzGYj7BEVZLiVrLBojo9h/0d0252427be368f32680daefc0c6b6a6/_10-_SOP__416.67___40-_x_200.png)\n\nNow you have 5 options or, in other words, the right to buy 5 shares of Netflix stock at 200.\n\nA couple of points not mentioned above for simplicity's sake: \n- We don’t grant fractional options so we always round down; any remaining amount of allocation is carried over to the next month. \n- When you first join your option allocation is prorated from your hire date."},{"sys":{"space":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"Space","id":"abx5xo923wy6"}},"id":"6LaqHSUAG1Kh5vYR1SkzJA","type":"Entry","createdAt":"2020-08-07T22:28:07.301Z","updatedAt":"2021-01-15T17:23:31.911Z","environment":{"sys":{"id":"master","type":"Link","linkType":"Environment"}},"revision":3,"contentType":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"ContentType","id":"sectionContent"}},"locale":"en-US"},"cmsTitle":"SOP \u003e Vest Schedule","sectionTitle":"Vest Schedule","sectionDescription":"Good news! Our options are immediately vested. This means that we can exercise our options whenever we would like, subject to insider trading restrictions."},{"sys":{"space":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"Space","id":"abx5xo923wy6"}},"id":"6pSNAGyQz5bci6QUXxCvmz","type":"Entry","createdAt":"2020-08-07T22:29:51.846Z","updatedAt":"2021-01-15T17:23:54.048Z","environment":{"sys":{"id":"master","type":"Link","linkType":"Environment"}},"revision":3,"contentType":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"ContentType","id":"sectionContent"}},"locale":"en-US"},"cmsTitle":"SOP \u003e Option Expiration","sectionTitle":"Option Expiration","sectionDescription":"Generally, your options will expire 10 years after the grant date, regardless of your employment status."},{"sys":{"space":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"Space","id":"abx5xo923wy6"}},"id":"2XRQ5etvAyc9dg9RU554N7","type":"Entry","createdAt":"2021-01-15T22:15:38.251Z","updatedAt":"2021-01-15T22:15:38.251Z","environment":{"sys":{"id":"master","type":"Link","linkType":"Environment"}},"revision":1,"contentType":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"ContentType","id":"sectionContent"}},"locale":"en-US"},"cmsTitle":"SOP Non-supplemental \u003e Understanding the Value of Your Options","sectionTitle":"Understanding the Value of Your Options","sectionDescription":"Before you exercise your options, you want to understand how to calculate your profit. Options are profitable when the current trading price of Netflix stock is higher than the exercise price at which it was granted to you.\n\nRemember from the example above where we were granted 5 options that had an exercise price of 200? Let’s assume you exercise those options when the market price of Netflix stock is 300. You’ll purchase each of the five shares at the exercise price of 200, sell them at 300, and make a profit of 100 for each option, or 500 total!\n\n![Value of the Free Options](//images.ctfassets.net/abx5xo923wy6/27a5P1XgXOAK8aWMG2COSI/395f275ac6eeacf669cbe58f41cae84b/ELP_Stock_Option_Program__SOP__Images.png)"}]}]},{"sys":{"space":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"Space","id":"abx5xo923wy6"}},"id":"4v7wEVJePS28TeDk0q9JYM","type":"Entry","createdAt":"2019-03-20T00:25:43.970Z","updatedAt":"2020-09-24T21:46:19.488Z","environment":{"sys":{"id":"master","type":"Link","linkType":"Environment"}},"revision":3,"contentType":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"ContentType","id":"locationBasedContent"}},"locale":"en-US"},"cmsTitle":"Ext Philippines - Financial","location":{"sys":{"space":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"Space","id":"abx5xo923wy6"}},"id":"4eQvIyr3XCpPK5q38684uY","type":"Entry","createdAt":"2019-02-14T21:18:42.106Z","updatedAt":"2020-11-05T16:33:13.931Z","environment":{"sys":{"id":"master","type":"Link","linkType":"Environment"}},"revision":8,"contentType":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"ContentType","id":"locationData"}},"locale":"en-US"},"cmsTitle":"Philippines","locationName":"Philippines","flag":{"sys":{"space":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"Space","id":"abx5xo923wy6"}},"id":"B7X8vnV9RVNGdh10awy3M","type":"Asset","createdAt":"2019-02-14T23:14:17.586Z","updatedAt":"2020-11-05T16:33:12.984Z","environment":{"sys":{"id":"master","type":"Link","linkType":"Environment"}},"revision":7,"locale":"en-US"},"title":"Philippines Flag","url":"//images.ctfassets.net/abx5xo923wy6/B7X8vnV9RVNGdh10awy3M/9e99518d2d095b2dc0f77edb4420583b/PH.svg","details":{"size":3200,"image":{"width":28,"height":20}},"fileName":"PH.svg","contentType":"image/svg+xml"},"slug":"philippines"},"locationSpecificContent":[{"sys":{"space":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"Space","id":"abx5xo923wy6"}},"id":"325FGHKT2MBLbAYrJucyc3","type":"Entry","createdAt":"2020-09-24T21:42:29.523Z","updatedAt":"2020-09-24T21:42:29.523Z","environment":{"sys":{"id":"master","type":"Link","linkType":"Environment"}},"revision":1,"contentType":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"ContentType","id":"sectionContent"}},"locale":"en-US"},"cmsTitle":"Ext - Global - Financial Philosophy ","sectionTitle":"Philosophy","sectionDescription":"At Netflix, we believe in top-of-personal-market compensation, providing employees the ability to save for retirement, a choice in the degree to which they participate in equity investment, and the option to make an impact on a global level by participating in our Employee Giving Program."},{"sys":{"space":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"Space","id":"abx5xo923wy6"}},"id":"793XreddvOOyWUy6qKmoG8","type":"Entry","createdAt":"2018-10-24T20:40:00.856Z","updatedAt":"2020-12-28T21:12:33.542Z","environment":{"sys":{"id":"master","type":"Link","linkType":"Environment"}},"revision":3,"contentType":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"ContentType","id":"sectionContent"}},"locale":"en-US"},"cmsTitle":"Ext Section - Employee Giving","sectionTitle":"Employee Giving","sectionDescription":"At Netflix, you have the ability to impact the world through the work you do. And we realize you may also want to make an impact in a more personal way. In the spirit of freedom and responsibility, you choose the organization(s) important to you, and Netflix will match your contribution $2 dollars for every $1 you donate up to $20,000 (or local currency equivalent."},{"sys":{"space":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"Space","id":"abx5xo923wy6"}},"id":"79hEZR4HmM0sjWipyohxrc","type":"Entry","createdAt":"2019-05-08T23:57:23.132Z","updatedAt":"2021-01-16T02:46:34.654Z","environment":{"sys":{"id":"master","type":"Link","linkType":"Environment"}},"revision":6,"contentType":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"ContentType","id":"sectionGroup"}},"locale":"en-US"},"cmsTitle":"Ext Mexico, Philippines, Brazil, Italy, Turkey Section Group - Stock Option Program (5% with supplemental)","title":"Stock Option Program (SOP)","content":[{"sys":{"space":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"Space","id":"abx5xo923wy6"}},"id":"ILVVvWgWAuUEyyuwqoOgM","type":"Entry","createdAt":"2018-10-31T20:26:07.647Z","updatedAt":"2021-01-15T17:22:26.544Z","environment":{"sys":{"id":"master","type":"Link","linkType":"Environment"}},"revision":5,"contentType":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"ContentType","id":"sectionContent"}},"locale":"en-US"},"cmsTitle":"SOP Philosophy","sectionTitle":"Philosophy","sectionDescription":"__The Why__\nThe Netflix Stock Option Program (SOP) is unique. At Netflix, we believe in top-of-personal-market pay and providing employees with a choice in the degree to which they invest in Netflix equity through the stock option program."},{"sys":{"space":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"Space","id":"abx5xo923wy6"}},"id":"1Pr9AeDAAfyFvD07WMHHBM","type":"Entry","createdAt":"2019-05-07T22:03:06.449Z","updatedAt":"2021-01-16T02:02:20.710Z","environment":{"sys":{"id":"master","type":"Link","linkType":"Environment"}},"revision":12,"contentType":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"ContentType","id":"sectionContent"}},"locale":"en-US"},"cmsTitle":"SOP - Overview (Pt 1 Internal and External Mexico, Brazil, Philippines, Italy)","sectionTitle":"Overview","sectionDescription":"## The Program\nYou have the opportunity to choose the amount of cash and equity you want to receive. The stock allocation is completely voluntary. If you’d like to receive options, you can allocate as much eligible salary to the SOP as you’d like. The program allows you to benefit from the growth of our stock price over time by accumulating options and then exercising them later when the price of the underlying Netflix stock has risen. \n\nFollowing your initial eligibility, you’ll be limited to maintaining or reducing your allocation during open enrollment for the next plan year, unless you receive a pay increase. In that instance you’ll be able to increase your allocation to an amount corresponding to the salary increase.\n\u003c/br\u003e\n## What is a stock option?\nA stock option is the right to purchase a share of Netflix stock at a predetermined price, called the exercise price. Options become valuable as the stock price appreciates above the exercise price. Netflix options are granted each month and expire 10 years from the grant date. \n\nA simple way to think of a stock option is to think of it like a coupon. The coupon is valuable to you when the regular price of the item is higher than what you can buy it for with your coupon, and once they expire they are longer valid. Let’s say you receive a coupon to buy an item at 100 until the printed expiration date. You go into the store and see that the retail price is 150. You redeem your coupon and buy it for 100, which saves you 50. In the context of stock options, you might have an option with an exercise price of 100. You exercise and sell your option later on when your stock price is 150, so your gain is 50!\n"},{"sys":{"space":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"Space","id":"abx5xo923wy6"}},"id":"nAKCdbZhkWaCgUUWe02S0","type":"Entry","createdAt":"2018-09-18T01:29:50.594Z","updatedAt":"2021-01-16T02:06:13.163Z","environment":{"sys":{"id":"master","type":"Link","linkType":"Environment"}},"revision":32,"contentType":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"ContentType","id":"sectionContent"}},"locale":"en-US"},"cmsTitle":"SOP \u003e Option Grants","sectionTitle":"Option Grants","sectionDescription":"Options are granted on the first trading day of each month. The exercise price of your options will be the closing price of Netflix stock on the day that the options are granted.\n\nGenerally, there are two factors that determine the number of options you receive: \n  1) the amount you are contributing to the program and \n  2) the cost of each option. \n\nWe calculate the monthly contribution by taking the annual amount that you’ve allocated and dividing it by twelve. The cost of each option is 40% of the exercise price. We’ll divide the monthly contribution by the cost of the option,  then we know how many options you should get for the month.\n\n![(5%) Your Annual Allocation / 12](//images.ctfassets.net/abx5xo923wy6/6nvGrFnyv7rtSH2OIT2EQE/40e04d877cb8c5bb47ca74762506c77f/_5-__Your_Annual_Allocation___12.png)\n\nAs an example, assume the following:\n- Your Annual Allocation: = $12,000 annually or $1,000 monthly\n- Closing Price on the Grant Day: $200\n\nMonthly Calculation:\n![(5% SOP) $1000 / 40% x $200](//images.ctfassets.net/abx5xo923wy6/Nc3FvMKTvwCAWZZbUYyhz/e3051ca4c9ef365725a8e3cd9a7450d7/_5-_SOP___1000___40-_x__200.png)\n\nNow you have 12 options or, in other words, the right to buy 12 shares of Netflix stock at $200.\n\nA couple of points not mentioned above for simplicity's sake:\n- We don’t grant fractional options so we always round down; any remaining amount of allocation is carried over to the next month.\n- When you first join your option allocation is prorated from your hire date.\n"},{"sys":{"space":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"Space","id":"abx5xo923wy6"}},"id":"6LaqHSUAG1Kh5vYR1SkzJA","type":"Entry","createdAt":"2020-08-07T22:28:07.301Z","updatedAt":"2021-01-15T17:23:31.911Z","environment":{"sys":{"id":"master","type":"Link","linkType":"Environment"}},"revision":3,"contentType":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"ContentType","id":"sectionContent"}},"locale":"en-US"},"cmsTitle":"SOP \u003e Vest Schedule","sectionTitle":"Vest Schedule","sectionDescription":"Good news! Our options are immediately vested. This means that we can exercise our options whenever we would like, subject to insider trading restrictions."},{"sys":{"space":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"Space","id":"abx5xo923wy6"}},"id":"6pSNAGyQz5bci6QUXxCvmz","type":"Entry","createdAt":"2020-08-07T22:29:51.846Z","updatedAt":"2021-01-15T17:23:54.048Z","environment":{"sys":{"id":"master","type":"Link","linkType":"Environment"}},"revision":3,"contentType":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"ContentType","id":"sectionContent"}},"locale":"en-US"},"cmsTitle":"SOP \u003e Option Expiration","sectionTitle":"Option Expiration","sectionDescription":"Generally, your options will expire 10 years after the grant date, regardless of your employment status."},{"sys":{"space":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"Space","id":"abx5xo923wy6"}},"id":"7cNJn2CgoeQFDsjyuh4Llz","type":"Entry","createdAt":"2021-01-15T19:10:51.128Z","updatedAt":"2021-01-15T22:05:32.553Z","environment":{"sys":{"id":"master","type":"Link","linkType":"Environment"}},"revision":2,"contentType":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"ContentType","id":"sectionContent"}},"locale":"en-US"},"cmsTitle":"Supplemental SOP \u003e Understanding the Value of Your Options","sectionTitle":"Understanding the Value of Your Options","sectionDescription":"Simply put, options gain value as the stock price appreciates above the exercise price. The higher the stock price goes above the exercise price, the more your options are worth.\nParticipating in the program is an investment choice that allows you to exchange salary for options. The salary you exchange goes to cover the cost of the options, which is 40% of the exercise price. You could consider  this as the premium you pay to get the right to buy a share at the exercise price. When thinking about the actual value of the options, you want to consider this 40% cost as your initial investment. \n\nIn our example above, we exchanged $80 of our salary to get each option with a $200 exercise price. If we have exchanged $80 of salary for each option to buy a share at $200, our total investment will be $280 per share.\n\nThe stock price would need to go up to at least $280 before we start to make a profit on the salary we exchanged, which means the stock value must appreciate by at least 40% above the exercise price. Continuing our example, let us assume that we exercise and sell our 5 options at $300. If we invested $280 per option and sold at $300, our profit is $20 per option, or $100 total***.\n\n![(5% SOP) (Sell Price - (Option Cost + Exercise Price)) * Number of Options](//images.ctfassets.net/abx5xo923wy6/7aoRJj75et1XNFknt1V0UI/402f86e62e2c17df64e863b1408ad8da/_5-_SOP___Sell_Price_-__Option_Cost___Exercise_Price_____Number_of_Options.png)\n\nThis doesn’t mean that you must wait until the stock price goes up at least 40% before you exercise however. You can exercise your options at any point, as long as the stock price is above the exercise price. \n\n***To keep the math simple, the above examples do not include taxes or fees."}]}]},{"sys":{"space":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"Space","id":"abx5xo923wy6"}},"id":"4S9u8gN9ILiANMYkb0b7kU","type":"Entry","createdAt":"2019-03-21T20:38:57.255Z","updatedAt":"2020-09-24T21:46:30.673Z","environment":{"sys":{"id":"master","type":"Link","linkType":"Environment"}},"revision":6,"contentType":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"ContentType","id":"locationBasedContent"}},"locale":"en-US"},"cmsTitle":"Ext Mexico - Financial","location":{"sys":{"space":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"Space","id":"abx5xo923wy6"}},"id":"5onoPlXBtycl8V6dxYdCuJ","type":"Entry","createdAt":"2019-03-20T16:37:44.848Z","updatedAt":"2020-11-05T16:33:14.640Z","environment":{"sys":{"id":"master","type":"Link","linkType":"Environment"}},"revision":6,"contentType":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"ContentType","id":"locationData"}},"locale":"en-US"},"cmsTitle":"Mexico","locationName":"Mexico","flag":{"sys":{"space":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"Space","id":"abx5xo923wy6"}},"id":"1ipyqCVgtL00lQrnWHaofE","type":"Asset","createdAt":"2019-03-20T16:37:38.833Z","updatedAt":"2020-11-05T16:33:13.006Z","environment":{"sys":{"id":"master","type":"Link","linkType":"Environment"}},"revision":5,"locale":"en-US"},"title":"Mexico Flag","url":"//images.ctfassets.net/abx5xo923wy6/1ipyqCVgtL00lQrnWHaofE/59aafb15f86dbd615ee8110e568369fe/MX.svg","details":{"size":1629,"image":{"width":28,"height":20}},"fileName":"MX.svg","contentType":"image/svg+xml"},"slug":"mexico"},"locationSpecificContent":[{"sys":{"space":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"Space","id":"abx5xo923wy6"}},"id":"325FGHKT2MBLbAYrJucyc3","type":"Entry","createdAt":"2020-09-24T21:42:29.523Z","updatedAt":"2020-09-24T21:42:29.523Z","environment":{"sys":{"id":"master","type":"Link","linkType":"Environment"}},"revision":1,"contentType":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"ContentType","id":"sectionContent"}},"locale":"en-US"},"cmsTitle":"Ext - Global - Financial Philosophy ","sectionTitle":"Philosophy","sectionDescription":"At Netflix, we believe in top-of-personal-market compensation, providing employees the ability to save for retirement, a choice in the degree to which they participate in equity investment, and the option to make an impact on a global level by participating in our Employee Giving Program."},{"sys":{"space":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"Space","id":"abx5xo923wy6"}},"id":"1E0SGd5dVNzFOm1LfmGkQo","type":"Entry","createdAt":"2019-03-21T20:38:53.335Z","updatedAt":"2020-07-30T20:51:23.248Z","environment":{"sys":{"id":"master","type":"Link","linkType":"Environment"}},"revision":6,"contentType":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"ContentType","id":"sectionContent"}},"locale":"en-US"},"cmsTitle":"Ext Mexico Section - Retirement Plan","sectionTitle":"Retirement Plan","sectionDescription":"Netflix helps you save for retirement with a DC retirement pension plan through GBM. Netflix provides all full time, regular employees a 2% fixed contribution, and employees can contribute up to 10% monthly salary. If an employee makes a voluntary contribution, Netflix will match up to an additional 5%."},{"sys":{"space":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"Space","id":"abx5xo923wy6"}},"id":"6tTPK0lS7uSgks2eca8SwI","type":"Entry","createdAt":"2018-10-25T21:06:37.957Z","updatedAt":"2020-12-28T21:12:49.393Z","environment":{"sys":{"id":"master","type":"Link","linkType":"Environment"}},"revision":3,"contentType":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"ContentType","id":"sectionContent"}},"locale":"en-US"},"cmsTitle":"Ext Global Section - Employee Giving","sectionTitle":"Employee Giving","sectionDescription":"At Netflix, you have the ability to impact the world through the work you do. And we realize you may also want to make an impact in a more personal way. In the spirit of freedom and responsibility, you choose the organization(s) important to you, and Netflix will match your contribution $2 dollars for every $1 you donate up to $20,000 (or local currency equivalent)."},{"sys":{"space":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"Space","id":"abx5xo923wy6"}},"id":"79hEZR4HmM0sjWipyohxrc","type":"Entry","createdAt":"2019-05-08T23:57:23.132Z","updatedAt":"2021-01-16T02:46:34.654Z","environment":{"sys":{"id":"master","type":"Link","linkType":"Environment"}},"revision":6,"contentType":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"ContentType","id":"sectionGroup"}},"locale":"en-US"},"cmsTitle":"Ext Mexico, Philippines, Brazil, Italy, Turkey Section Group - Stock Option Program (5% with supplemental)","title":"Stock Option Program (SOP)","content":[{"sys":{"space":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"Space","id":"abx5xo923wy6"}},"id":"ILVVvWgWAuUEyyuwqoOgM","type":"Entry","createdAt":"2018-10-31T20:26:07.647Z","updatedAt":"2021-01-15T17:22:26.544Z","environment":{"sys":{"id":"master","type":"Link","linkType":"Environment"}},"revision":5,"contentType":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"ContentType","id":"sectionContent"}},"locale":"en-US"},"cmsTitle":"SOP Philosophy","sectionTitle":"Philosophy","sectionDescription":"__The Why__\nThe Netflix Stock Option Program (SOP) is unique. At Netflix, we believe in top-of-personal-market pay and providing employees with a choice in the degree to which they invest in Netflix equity through the stock option program."},{"sys":{"space":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"Space","id":"abx5xo923wy6"}},"id":"1Pr9AeDAAfyFvD07WMHHBM","type":"Entry","createdAt":"2019-05-07T22:03:06.449Z","updatedAt":"2021-01-16T02:02:20.710Z","environment":{"sys":{"id":"master","type":"Link","linkType":"Environment"}},"revision":12,"contentType":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"ContentType","id":"sectionContent"}},"locale":"en-US"},"cmsTitle":"SOP - Overview (Pt 1 Internal and External Mexico, Brazil, Philippines, Italy)","sectionTitle":"Overview","sectionDescription":"## The Program\nYou have the opportunity to choose the amount of cash and equity you want to receive. The stock allocation is completely voluntary. If you’d like to receive options, you can allocate as much eligible salary to the SOP as you’d like. The program allows you to benefit from the growth of our stock price over time by accumulating options and then exercising them later when the price of the underlying Netflix stock has risen. \n\nFollowing your initial eligibility, you’ll be limited to maintaining or reducing your allocation during open enrollment for the next plan year, unless you receive a pay increase. In that instance you’ll be able to increase your allocation to an amount corresponding to the salary increase.\n\u003c/br\u003e\n## What is a stock option?\nA stock option is the right to purchase a share of Netflix stock at a predetermined price, called the exercise price. Options become valuable as the stock price appreciates above the exercise price. Netflix options are granted each month and expire 10 years from the grant date. \n\nA simple way to think of a stock option is to think of it like a coupon. The coupon is valuable to you when the regular price of the item is higher than what you can buy it for with your coupon, and once they expire they are longer valid. Let’s say you receive a coupon to buy an item at 100 until the printed expiration date. You go into the store and see that the retail price is 150. You redeem your coupon and buy it for 100, which saves you 50. In the context of stock options, you might have an option with an exercise price of 100. You exercise and sell your option later on when your stock price is 150, so your gain is 50!\n"},{"sys":{"space":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"Space","id":"abx5xo923wy6"}},"id":"nAKCdbZhkWaCgUUWe02S0","type":"Entry","createdAt":"2018-09-18T01:29:50.594Z","updatedAt":"2021-01-16T02:06:13.163Z","environment":{"sys":{"id":"master","type":"Link","linkType":"Environment"}},"revision":32,"contentType":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"ContentType","id":"sectionContent"}},"locale":"en-US"},"cmsTitle":"SOP \u003e Option Grants","sectionTitle":"Option Grants","sectionDescription":"Options are granted on the first trading day of each month. The exercise price of your options will be the closing price of Netflix stock on the day that the options are granted.\n\nGenerally, there are two factors that determine the number of options you receive: \n  1) the amount you are contributing to the program and \n  2) the cost of each option. \n\nWe calculate the monthly contribution by taking the annual amount that you’ve allocated and dividing it by twelve. The cost of each option is 40% of the exercise price. We’ll divide the monthly contribution by the cost of the option,  then we know how many options you should get for the month.\n\n![(5%) Your Annual Allocation / 12](//images.ctfassets.net/abx5xo923wy6/6nvGrFnyv7rtSH2OIT2EQE/40e04d877cb8c5bb47ca74762506c77f/_5-__Your_Annual_Allocation___12.png)\n\nAs an example, assume the following:\n- Your Annual Allocation: = $12,000 annually or $1,000 monthly\n- Closing Price on the Grant Day: $200\n\nMonthly Calculation:\n![(5% SOP) $1000 / 40% x $200](//images.ctfassets.net/abx5xo923wy6/Nc3FvMKTvwCAWZZbUYyhz/e3051ca4c9ef365725a8e3cd9a7450d7/_5-_SOP___1000___40-_x__200.png)\n\nNow you have 12 options or, in other words, the right to buy 12 shares of Netflix stock at $200.\n\nA couple of points not mentioned above for simplicity's sake:\n- We don’t grant fractional options so we always round down; any remaining amount of allocation is carried over to the next month.\n- When you first join your option allocation is prorated from your hire date.\n"},{"sys":{"space":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"Space","id":"abx5xo923wy6"}},"id":"6LaqHSUAG1Kh5vYR1SkzJA","type":"Entry","createdAt":"2020-08-07T22:28:07.301Z","updatedAt":"2021-01-15T17:23:31.911Z","environment":{"sys":{"id":"master","type":"Link","linkType":"Environment"}},"revision":3,"contentType":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"ContentType","id":"sectionContent"}},"locale":"en-US"},"cmsTitle":"SOP \u003e Vest Schedule","sectionTitle":"Vest Schedule","sectionDescription":"Good news! Our options are immediately vested. This means that we can exercise our options whenever we would like, subject to insider trading restrictions."},{"sys":{"space":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"Space","id":"abx5xo923wy6"}},"id":"6pSNAGyQz5bci6QUXxCvmz","type":"Entry","createdAt":"2020-08-07T22:29:51.846Z","updatedAt":"2021-01-15T17:23:54.048Z","environment":{"sys":{"id":"master","type":"Link","linkType":"Environment"}},"revision":3,"contentType":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"ContentType","id":"sectionContent"}},"locale":"en-US"},"cmsTitle":"SOP \u003e Option Expiration","sectionTitle":"Option Expiration","sectionDescription":"Generally, your options will expire 10 years after the grant date, regardless of your employment status."},{"sys":{"space":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"Space","id":"abx5xo923wy6"}},"id":"7cNJn2CgoeQFDsjyuh4Llz","type":"Entry","createdAt":"2021-01-15T19:10:51.128Z","updatedAt":"2021-01-15T22:05:32.553Z","environment":{"sys":{"id":"master","type":"Link","linkType":"Environment"}},"revision":2,"contentType":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"ContentType","id":"sectionContent"}},"locale":"en-US"},"cmsTitle":"Supplemental SOP \u003e Understanding the Value of Your Options","sectionTitle":"Understanding the Value of Your Options","sectionDescription":"Simply put, options gain value as the stock price appreciates above the exercise price. The higher the stock price goes above the exercise price, the more your options are worth.\nParticipating in the program is an investment choice that allows you to exchange salary for options. The salary you exchange goes to cover the cost of the options, which is 40% of the exercise price. You could consider  this as the premium you pay to get the right to buy a share at the exercise price. When thinking about the actual value of the options, you want to consider this 40% cost as your initial investment. \n\nIn our example above, we exchanged $80 of our salary to get each option with a $200 exercise price. If we have exchanged $80 of salary for each option to buy a share at $200, our total investment will be $280 per share.\n\nThe stock price would need to go up to at least $280 before we start to make a profit on the salary we exchanged, which means the stock value must appreciate by at least 40% above the exercise price. Continuing our example, let us assume that we exercise and sell our 5 options at $300. If we invested $280 per option and sold at $300, our profit is $20 per option, or $100 total***.\n\n![(5% SOP) (Sell Price - (Option Cost + Exercise Price)) * Number of Options](//images.ctfassets.net/abx5xo923wy6/7aoRJj75et1XNFknt1V0UI/402f86e62e2c17df64e863b1408ad8da/_5-_SOP___Sell_Price_-__Option_Cost___Exercise_Price_____Number_of_Options.png)\n\nThis doesn’t mean that you must wait until the stock price goes up at least 40% before you exercise however. You can exercise your options at any point, as long as the stock price is above the exercise price. \n\n***To keep the math simple, the above examples do not include taxes or fees."}]}]},{"sys":{"space":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"Space","id":"abx5xo923wy6"}},"id":"21uJ6lzp6YUs5ZYpjP8ebd","type":"Entry","createdAt":"2019-06-11T20:10:40.158Z","updatedAt":"2020-09-24T21:46:45.155Z","environment":{"sys":{"id":"master","type":"Link","linkType":"Environment"}},"revision":2,"contentType":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType